00:21:53.122 --> 00:21:54.704
Why don't we get married, Kiran?

00:21:56.186 --> 00:21:57.186
What?!

00:21:58.134 --> 00:21:59.134
I'm serious.

00:22:03.053 --> 00:22:04.815
I've never thought about it.

00:22:07.284 --> 00:22:11.015
-I've only think about one thing.
-What?

00:22:12.811 --> 00:22:14.597
Music and my career.

00:22:16.901 --> 00:22:19.114
I want to make the
greatest singer of the land.

00:22:21.728 --> 00:22:24.013
-That'll be difficult.
-Why?

00:22:24.561 --> 00:22:27.665
Because that status has been
booked for me a long while ago.

00:22:30.486 --> 00:22:31.486
Kiran.

00:22:34.761 --> 00:22:38.199
What could be better
for both of us?

00:22:39.493 --> 00:22:42.558
We travel towards same goals. And
we could reach our goal together.

00:22:45.434 --> 00:22:48.058
Tell me... will you marry me?

00:22:50.535 --> 00:22:52.144
What brings you here?

00:22:52.344 --> 00:22:54.310
He's a famous singer.

00:22:55.376 --> 00:22:56.376
So you are a singer, are you?

00:22:57.662 --> 00:23:00.516
Actually, I'm a composer.

00:23:01.837 --> 00:23:03.956
I write the songs I sing.

00:23:04.096 --> 00:23:04.919
Classicals?

00:23:04.999 --> 00:23:11.079
-Not classicals. I sing lighter tunes.
-How light?

00:23:12.933 --> 00:23:15.027
-I don't think you understand.
-Please help me too.

00:23:15.143 --> 00:23:17.828
I sing songs that strike
a chord in the heart.

00:23:19.572 --> 00:23:20.838
And where do you sing such songs?

00:23:21.918 --> 00:23:24.478
Presently, I sing at a hotel.
-At a hotel?

00:23:26.560 --> 00:23:30.233
One might as well sing at a hotel
as go around with a begging bowl.

00:23:30.421 --> 00:23:34.378
As with wandering minstrels who
collect pence in tips if at all.

00:23:34.458 --> 00:23:37.884
Enough. I have not come
here to discuss my careers.

00:23:37.985 --> 00:23:39.508
So, what brings you here?

00:23:43.850 --> 00:23:45.200
Excuse me, Kiran.

00:23:45.541 --> 00:23:47.831
Stop, Rohit!

00:23:48.863 --> 00:23:50.213
Listen to me...

00:23:50.857 --> 00:23:54.130
Rohit... Please Rohit.

00:23:57.526 --> 00:24:00.896
I didn't invite Rohit
so you might insult him.

00:24:01.565 --> 00:24:06.649
D'you take me for a fool? A look at
him and I know why you invited him.

00:24:07.964 --> 00:24:10.617
Stop being foolish. Your
marriage has already been fixed.

00:24:15.415 --> 00:24:19.308
-I'm in love with Rohit.
-Do you hear what she says?

00:24:21.604 --> 00:24:25.342
You must consider the
consequences. This is not done.

00:24:26.015 --> 00:24:29.933
The upbringing and education I've
given her all these years are a waste!

00:24:30.479 --> 00:24:32.983
If you think so highly about my
upbringing and my education...

00:24:33.130 --> 00:24:35.156
...you should respect
my decisions too.

00:24:35.461 --> 00:24:38.985
I have a feeling that he's a
cunning fellow. He's ensnaring you.

00:24:40.069 --> 00:24:42.902
-You're still an innocent girl.
-I'm no innocent, mother.

00:24:43.064 --> 00:24:44.664
And what does that make of you?

00:24:45.507 --> 00:24:47.599
I'm an artist.
And, he's an artist too.

00:24:47.958 --> 00:24:49.744
You can't gauge our sentiments.

00:24:50.673 --> 00:24:51.764
Don't I understand?

00:24:52.150 --> 00:24:54.328
An artist my foot!
A Bremen-town musician!

00:24:54.830 --> 00:24:57.323
A good for nothing vagabond!
And she wants to marry him!

00:24:57.505 --> 00:24:59.347
You'll get to know about the
realities in life in no time!

00:24:59.655 --> 00:25:03.281
Don't you come back crying later on.
Our doors will have closed for you.

00:25:06.893 --> 00:25:12.251
Just as well that you told me all
this. It'll help me take my decision.

00:25:13.715 --> 00:25:15.515
I'm going to marry Rohit.

00:25:16.120 --> 00:25:17.578
Kiran... Kir...

00:26:28.657 --> 00:26:29.657
Enough.

00:26:29.997 --> 00:26:33.497
-I'll floor them at the audition today.
-May I accompany you?

00:26:33.577 --> 00:26:35.018
It'll take me 2
minutes to get dressed.

00:26:36.668 --> 00:26:38.586
Isn't the plumber
expected in today?

00:26:39.759 --> 00:26:41.084
See you. Bye.

00:26:48.905 --> 00:26:49.905
Thank you.

00:27:23.134 --> 00:27:25.398
How are you going to climb four
stories in the condition you are?

00:27:25.632 --> 00:27:28.006
But, this is your first recording.
And I wanted to be there with you.

00:27:28.086 --> 00:27:30.765
I'm not recording for a film. Its
just a jingle for an advertisement.

00:27:31.906 --> 00:27:34.460
When am I going to meet the right
people? When will I start working?

00:27:34.937 --> 00:27:37.390
It's just a matter of a few more
months. What makes you so upright?

00:28:23.198 --> 00:28:24.985
-Hello, Farida. Come in.
-What are you doing?

00:28:25.065 --> 00:28:27.096
Nothing much. Just cooking.

00:28:27.361 --> 00:28:29.822
-Like a cup of tea? -Why not?
-Is the tea brewed? -Yes.

00:28:30.989 --> 00:28:32.747
I haven't seen you
around in 4 or 5 days.

00:28:33.471 --> 00:28:35.250
-Have you been keeping well?
-Absolutely.

00:28:37.611 --> 00:28:41.905
-What's the matter? You seem tense.
-Not at all. I'm perfectly fine.

00:28:45.161 --> 00:28:46.927
How are your music
rehearsals going on?

00:28:47.397 --> 00:28:51.231
I hardly find time outside household
chores. How am I to rehearse?

00:28:52.882 --> 00:28:56.939
What of the career in music? Can you
immerse yourself so in the chores?

00:28:58.284 --> 00:29:00.557
You must carve out some
time everyday for rehearsing.

00:29:01.312 --> 00:29:04.945
Look at me... I must fetch Sonu
from school after I finish cooking.

00:29:05.651 --> 00:29:09.966
I'll go and fetch Sonu... Yes.
I will. It doesn't really matter.

00:29:10.274 --> 00:29:11.274
Thanks.

00:29:13.524 --> 00:29:14.524
Hi, Kiran.

00:29:14.718 --> 00:29:16.300
Will you please draw a bath for me?
Make it fast.

00:29:16.394 --> 00:29:17.394
I've to attend a party.

00:29:17.487 --> 00:29:19.954
-What party? -Oh, there's
something I'd like you to know.

00:29:20.582 --> 00:29:24.234
-I've dumped the job.
-Why?

00:29:24.810 --> 00:29:28.843
I had enough of Mehra's abuses.
Besides, I want to move upwards.

00:29:29.589 --> 00:29:34.617
-What's more, I met Gulbadan
Kumar today. -Gulbadan Kumar?

00:29:34.793 --> 00:29:37.922
Yes. He owns Prince Records. Its
really tough to get to meet him.

00:29:38.381 --> 00:29:42.391
I walked into his office and sang
a few songs. He liked my voice.

00:29:42.834 --> 00:29:47.734
He invited me to the party this
evening. Looks like I've made it.

00:29:48.584 --> 00:29:50.067
Just press these clothes for me,
will you?

00:29:50.226 --> 00:29:51.440
I'm coming with you!

00:29:51.718 --> 00:29:52.445
What'll you do there?

00:29:52.525 --> 00:29:54.332
-You'd get bored.
-No. I won't get bored.

00:29:55.001 --> 00:29:57.548
-What about Sonu?
-Farida can put him to sleep.

00:29:58.678 --> 00:30:01.192
All right. You can come along.
Get dressed in some good clothes.

00:30:01.361 --> 00:30:03.042
Now. Take the clothes.
Press them quickly.

00:30:08.568 --> 00:30:10.106
Congratulations, Mr.
Gulbadan Kumar.

00:30:10.261 --> 00:30:14.245
Ever since your company was formed
music sales have grown manifold.

00:30:14.651 --> 00:30:16.186
It's the grace
of The Divine Mother.

00:30:18.840 --> 00:30:20.841
A double gold disc
for the music directors.

00:30:21.188 --> 00:30:22.656
Someday I'll get mine too.

00:30:25.502 --> 00:30:28.497
I've recorded my voice
on a cassette... Rohit!

00:30:29.106 --> 00:30:31.254
I've recorded one of
my songs in a cassette.

00:30:31.345 --> 00:30:33.935
Will you please give it
to Gulbadan Kumar?

00:30:34.865 --> 00:30:36.515
All right.

00:30:38.315 --> 00:30:42.666
Hows the good lady? I greet you
in the name of The Divine Mother.

00:30:42.800 --> 00:30:46.543
-Hello. -I'm Rohit Kumar.
-Of course, Mr. Rohit Kumar.

00:30:46.631 --> 00:30:49.176
-Greetings!
-Grand party. -It's modest really.

00:30:50.043 --> 00:30:53.858
-Have you listened to my cassette?
-Yes I did. -Did you like it?

00:30:54.545 --> 00:30:56.749
-Very nice.
-Thank you, Sir. Thank you, Sir.

00:31:00.883 --> 00:31:03.634
Glory be to The Divine Mother!

00:31:04.152 --> 00:31:07.368
Congratulations, Mr. Gulbadan!
You're raking in gold discs.

00:31:07.596 --> 00:31:08.992
Let's pose for a photograph.

00:31:11.565 --> 00:31:14.273
-You're the biggest of them all.
-Not at all. -Isn't it, now?

00:31:14.381 --> 00:31:19.834
It's the two of you, Messrs Amar &
Kaushik who are the most well known.

00:31:19.955 --> 00:31:25.116
That's the magic of our music.
We've defined 6 super hit films.

00:31:25.314 --> 00:31:27.623
-Our critics are now silenced.
-Indeed. Indeed, Mr. Gulbadan.

00:31:27.716 --> 00:31:30.741
You must listen to the music
we've scored for our next film.

00:31:31.146 --> 00:31:33.531
We recorded a song yesterday.
Beautiful!

00:31:35.751 --> 00:31:37.320
Which film is the song meant for?

00:31:37.640 --> 00:31:41.984
Well... he's an upcoming
artiste. He's also a singer.

00:31:42.202 --> 00:31:44.587
-Mr. Rahul Kumar.
-I'm Rohit Kumar, Sir.

00:31:44.667 --> 00:31:46.069
Oh yes... Mr. Rohit Kumar.

00:31:46.551 --> 00:31:47.942
-Do you sing?
-Yes, Sir.

00:31:48.277 --> 00:31:50.378
I see. For whom have
you sung till now?

00:31:51.110 --> 00:31:53.594
-Nothing special yet.
-Yes. Go on.

00:31:53.817 --> 00:31:55.169
I want to sing for you.

00:31:55.249 --> 00:31:56.561
-Of course.
-Thank you.

00:31:58.144 --> 00:32:00.180
-Don't forget to give my cassette.
-Oh yes. But, stop it now, will you?

00:32:02.151 --> 00:32:04.086
-Yes... what is it?
-I'm not only a singer.

00:32:04.175 --> 00:32:06.904
I've written a few songs too.

00:32:07.127 --> 00:32:08.840
-And what are you?
-A composer.

00:32:10.312 --> 00:32:12.872
In a country like ours, just
about anyone can turn a composer.

00:32:15.223 --> 00:32:20.442
Call me up on Monday. If your
voice is worth it, you're made.

00:32:21.590 --> 00:32:23.615
I'll come over on Monday
after giving you a call.

00:32:23.814 --> 00:32:25.566
-What more could you want?
Hail mother. -Mr. Gulbadan

00:32:25.652 --> 00:32:26.652
Yes, Sir.

00:32:27.150 --> 00:32:29.318
Why aren't you giving
him my cassette?

00:32:29.648 --> 00:32:31.332
-I can't give the cassette now.
-Why?

00:32:31.869 --> 00:32:33.985
It was so difficult getting an
audition for myself. -So what?

00:32:34.542 --> 00:32:36.694
How can I ask them to
audition my wife too?

00:32:36.876 --> 00:32:38.583
They'll think I'm trying to force
my family down their throats.

00:32:38.745 --> 00:32:40.873
Please cheers for amar kaushik.

00:32:57.400 --> 00:32:59.656
So, d'you feel that I'm
imposing myself upon you?

00:33:00.930 --> 00:33:01.930
I never said that.

00:33:02.387 --> 00:33:05.963
-That's what you meant! -I'm tired
and I don't want to get into a fight.

00:33:06.161 --> 00:33:07.730
D'you mean to say that
I want to get into a fight?

00:33:07.862 --> 00:33:09.030
Sonu is sleeping.

00:33:09.598 --> 00:33:13.550
I'd only asked you to
hand over my cassette.

00:33:14.713 --> 00:33:16.495
Was it so difficult?

00:33:17.033 --> 00:33:21.033
I haven't heard what you've recorded.
I don't even know what's in it.

00:33:21.341 --> 00:33:22.555
I don't know if
it's worth a hearing.

00:33:22.719 --> 00:33:24.223
And, it was tough
getting an audition.

00:33:24.517 --> 00:33:26.771
Must I lose a chance by
trying to push your cassette?

00:33:29.785 --> 00:33:33.634
An hour ago, you loved my voice.
Now, it isn't worth auditioning!

00:33:33.776 --> 00:33:34.950
I don't mean that.

00:33:35.146 --> 00:33:37.263
-One must practice regularly to be
able to sing properly. -Practice.

00:33:37.476 --> 00:33:40.536
Just another excuse! And I think
I understand you perfectly, Rohit.

00:33:40.958 --> 00:33:45.369
You've been pursuing your career.
And all I get are flimsy excuses.

00:33:45.449 --> 00:33:46.340
Please don't scream.

00:33:46.420 --> 00:33:50.746
Why don't you say it plainly?
That I don't have the aesthetics.

00:33:51.320 --> 00:33:53.935
That I should stop dreaming about
becoming a professional singer.

00:33:54.580 --> 00:33:56.352
That's not what's
going to be, Rohit.

00:33:56.890 --> 00:34:02.467
I won't give up! And you for one,
cannot break my resolve! Get that?

00:34:06.788 --> 00:34:11.074
I don't know why Rohit is doing
this. He mustn't do this to you.

00:34:11.474 --> 00:34:14.030
-It's wrong on his part. -We've
finished our homework, Mother.

00:34:14.152 --> 00:34:15.257
May we go to play?

00:34:15.741 --> 00:34:17.745
-Make sure you return soon.
-All right.

00:34:22.118 --> 00:34:26.419
You have the right to a career. Why
don't you discuss it with Rohit?

00:34:31.264 --> 00:34:33.829
What are you doing here?
I've been looking for you so long.

00:34:34.393 --> 00:34:36.256
-I had to discuss some things
with Farida. -What?

00:34:36.835 --> 00:34:38.876
Besides Sonu is getting on my
nerves. Who is to take care of him?

00:34:39.039 --> 00:34:41.816
I have to go to a rehearsal. Where
are my clothes? How about some food?

00:34:42.507 --> 00:34:45.939
-I'm coming over.
-And, where's the file of my songs?

00:34:46.232 --> 00:34:48.348
I've been looking for it all
day. I just can't find it.

00:34:48.551 --> 00:34:50.670
I'd brought it down with
me for my practice session.

00:34:56.722 --> 00:34:59.258
Why don't you just sit over here
for the rest of the day practicing!

00:34:59.655 --> 00:35:00.519
-I said I'm coming.
-Don't bother.

00:35:00.599 --> 00:35:02.026
You can practice singing
for the rest of the day.

00:35:02.128 --> 00:35:03.331
I'll feed myself at a restaurant.

00:35:03.569 --> 00:35:06.365
-I'll look after the household too.
-Have I ever refused to do all that?

00:35:16.457 --> 00:35:20.210
-What've you done? -Sorry, Mother.
-You've got my washing all dirty.

00:35:20.403 --> 00:35:24.630
I've been at the laundry for 2 hours.
And I've asked you not to play here.

00:35:25.905 --> 00:35:28.587
How many times have
I asked you not to play?!

00:35:30.063 --> 00:35:31.896
What's up, Kiran?
Why did you beat him?

00:35:32.160 --> 00:35:33.242
What has he done?

00:35:33.424 --> 00:35:37.137
He won't listen to me. And now,
he's got the laundry all dirty.

00:35:38.648 --> 00:35:43.180
I'm sick and tired of chorus
all day. I've gone out of my mind.

00:35:48.721 --> 00:35:49.721
Kiran...

00:35:54.298 --> 00:35:55.298
Kiran.

00:35:56.963 --> 00:36:00.277
We tread upon the same path, Kiran.
What could be better for both of us?

00:36:01.822 --> 00:36:04.576
Our destination is same.
We'll reach there together.

00:36:23.125 --> 00:36:27.247
I am sorry sonu... sorry.

00:36:33.339 --> 00:36:34.342
I love you.

00:36:43.144 --> 00:36:44.144
Kiran...

00:36:45.407 --> 00:36:46.407
Kiran.

00:36:47.552 --> 00:36:48.978
Open up, quickly.

00:36:50.183 --> 00:36:52.506
Come on, hurry up.

00:36:54.003 --> 00:36:56.644
Make sure to remember
the day today.

00:36:57.405 --> 00:36:59.242
We'll celebrate
this day every year.

00:36:59.322 --> 00:37:00.934
This is the day
I've awaited forever.

00:37:01.118 --> 00:37:02.800
The day on which
my career commences!

00:37:02.921 --> 00:37:06.770
Today was the day! Amar-Kaushik were
left speechless after I auditioned.

00:37:07.524 --> 00:37:10.254
I'm singing the first song
for Pawan Chopra's new film.

00:37:11.553 --> 00:37:12.553
I'm leaving, Rohit.

00:37:13.467 --> 00:37:17.296
And they said that if this song
passes the muster while recording...

00:37:17.519 --> 00:37:19.735
...I'll get to sing all the songs
for the film. I'm recording tomorrow.

00:37:20.188 --> 00:37:22.377
-Want to come along?
-I said I'm leaving.

00:37:23.779 --> 00:37:25.728
-Where are you going?
-Here are the keys to the house.

00:37:26.140 --> 00:37:28.884
These are the rationing cards...
and here are the bills for the month.

00:37:29.261 --> 00:37:30.778
I've paid all the bills.

00:37:31.229 --> 00:37:33.184
You'll find the balance of
the money in the cupboard.

00:37:34.025 --> 00:37:37.514
Here's the electricity bill. Make
sure you pay it up by the weekend.

00:37:40.296 --> 00:37:41.418
I'm leaving you.

00:37:42.358 --> 00:37:45.041
Wait a minute! What are
you saying? What's happened?

00:37:45.325 --> 00:37:47.726
-Have I done anything wrong?
-No, you haven't.

00:37:47.836 --> 00:37:49.220
-What's it then? Tell me.
-Don't touch me!

00:37:50.057 --> 00:37:52.796
-Just let me go. -But why are
you leaving? Say something!

00:37:52.947 --> 00:37:54.760
Why don't you understand!

00:37:56.846 --> 00:37:58.909
It isn't just an
isolated something.

00:37:59.486 --> 00:38:01.136
It might be my mistake too.

00:38:03.450 --> 00:38:05.705
-Something is happening to me.
-What's this with you?

00:38:06.832 --> 00:38:10.158
-I don't know! -It's nothing more
than a figment of your imagination.

00:38:11.371 --> 00:38:13.326
Please, let me go.

00:38:14.235 --> 00:38:15.855
I must make a life for myself.

00:38:16.205 --> 00:38:17.677
But this and here,
is what your life is!

00:38:17.757 --> 00:38:20.357
No! This is your life,
only yours.

00:38:21.767 --> 00:38:23.307
And I want to handle myself.

00:38:24.703 --> 00:38:26.481
Else, I'll go out of my mind.

00:38:28.562 --> 00:38:30.324
So you want to walk
out of this marriage.

00:38:32.219 --> 00:38:33.599
But what of Sonu?

00:38:34.096 --> 00:38:35.543
How can you walk out on him?

00:38:35.635 --> 00:38:36.635
I love him.

00:38:40.086 --> 00:38:41.518
But, he's better off without me.

00:38:41.676 --> 00:38:45.707
Oh God! I don't believe this!
Kiran! Why are you doing this to me?!

00:38:46.534 --> 00:38:50.142
I've just got my golden chance. And
here you are... walking out on me!

00:38:51.945 --> 00:38:56.061
I need you, Kiran. If you stand by
me, I can even reach for the stars.

00:38:57.481 --> 00:38:59.899
But you had told me that we'd
reach out for the stars together.

00:39:04.469 --> 00:39:06.931
D'you feel that I'm trying to
stop you from becoming a singer?

00:39:07.477 --> 00:39:09.972
You might dream of
becoming a singer.

00:39:10.900 --> 00:39:13.715
But don't expect me to go around
singing false praises for you.

00:39:15.558 --> 00:39:17.427
Look, I am sorry.

00:39:18.267 --> 00:39:21.505
I lost my head. I agree that
both of us have made mistakes.

00:39:21.963 --> 00:39:24.611
But that doesn't mean that you must
walk out of your home. Isn't that so?

00:39:24.814 --> 00:39:27.861
We can always mend our
ways. Now, come in.

00:39:29.990 --> 00:39:32.161
Now you're being stubborn.
Just like your parents.

00:39:32.958 --> 00:39:36.018
-Don't drag my parents into this.
-Why not? You carry the same traits.

00:39:36.252 --> 00:39:37.822
Now, are you going to
stop taunting my parents?!

00:39:37.902 --> 00:39:40.266
Won't I! They haven't been able
to achieve anything in life.

00:39:40.454 --> 00:39:42.018
And they're jealous of others.

00:39:44.786 --> 00:39:47.591
And d'you think I'm jealous
of your success? -Yes!

00:39:50.072 --> 00:39:53.005
Thank you very much.
I won't ever forget that.

00:39:53.767 --> 00:39:58.825
I'd rather suffer my traits than
your taunts for the rest of my life.

00:40:20.802 --> 00:40:21.802
Rohit...

00:40:22.371 --> 00:40:23.507
Where has Kiran gone?

00:40:24.646 --> 00:40:27.315
-What I should be asking you?
-Why me?

00:40:27.395 --> 00:40:29.534
She used to spend more than half
her working hours in your company.

00:40:29.845 --> 00:40:33.583
And the two of you must've more
than discussed my weak points.

00:40:33.963 --> 00:40:36.964
Forget all that.
Kiran has left you.

00:40:37.222 --> 00:40:39.247
-We must do something about it.
-Not "we". It's I who has to do.

00:40:39.405 --> 00:40:40.999
And I'll do whatever must be done.

00:40:41.379 --> 00:40:42.219
Rohit.

00:40:42.299 --> 00:40:45.887
You must try to understand it now
or never. Kiran is very unhappy.

00:40:46.134 --> 00:40:48.506
-And the fact is that...
-Fact remains that of the past 6 years...

00:40:48.633 --> 00:40:52.079
...I've been trying heart
and soul to get a break...

00:40:52.212 --> 00:40:54.243
...so that my career can take
off; so that my life shapes up!

00:40:54.538 --> 00:40:57.921
After 6 long years, I get a break.
I'm slated to sing for Amar-Kaushik!

00:40:58.299 --> 00:41:00.183
I took a cab home as soon as
I got to know; so that I could...

00:41:00.263 --> 00:41:02.575
...share the greatest
moment of my life with her.

00:41:02.655 --> 00:41:04.707
And she tells me that she's
walking out of my life.

00:41:05.591 --> 00:41:06.767
What does it mean?!

00:41:06.858 --> 00:41:10.377
She couldn't share the
greatest moment of your life.

00:41:11.073 --> 00:41:16.269
-It's your life, after all.
-You're fantastic! Your fabulous.

00:41:17.792 --> 00:41:21.624
That your husband deserted
you because you were unhappy...

00:41:21.909 --> 00:41:24.323
...doesn't mean that every woman
is unhappy with her husband.

00:41:28.946 --> 00:41:32.508
I haven't come here to discuss my
husband. I'm concerned about Kiran.

00:41:33.203 --> 00:41:36.002
-You may keep your concern within
your confines. -I shall.

00:41:36.622 --> 00:41:39.862
Before I leave, let me tell you that
you could never understand Kiran.

00:41:40.569 --> 00:41:42.930
She is no petty woman to serve
as a part of your interior decor.

00:41:43.469 --> 00:41:47.526
She had her own dreams. And it takes
courage for a woman to walk out.

00:41:48.529 --> 00:41:49.529
Yes!

00:41:49.767 --> 00:41:53.525
And it takes more to walk out on
a helpless child. Isn't that so?

00:42:27.935 --> 00:42:31.266
Daddy... daddy... daddy... daddy.

00:42:31.625 --> 00:42:35.890
-Why are you sleeping here?
-Oh... what? -And where's Mummy?

00:42:36.626 --> 00:42:37.855
Ohh! God!

00:42:39.895 --> 00:42:42.870
-Tell me... Where's Mummy?
-What's the time now?

00:42:44.005 --> 00:42:46.472
The small hand is on 7.
And the big hand is on 3.

00:42:48.308 --> 00:42:50.785
I'm going to be late
for the recording.

00:42:50.865 --> 00:42:55.045
-Tell me, Daddy... where's Mummy?
-Wait a minute.

00:42:59.068 --> 00:43:02.891
-You mother has gone to your aunt's.
-Which aunt?

00:43:03.465 --> 00:43:07.282
-The one in Pune.
-Aunt Ratna lives there.

00:43:07.420 --> 00:43:09.079
That's where she has gone.

00:43:09.227 --> 00:43:13.427
-When is she going to come back?
-Very soon... in 3 or 4 days.

00:43:14.019 --> 00:43:15.899
Now make a move.
I've got to get ready.

00:43:18.316 --> 00:43:21.847
-Who's going to get me
ready for school? -I will, son.

00:43:23.564 --> 00:43:25.643
-And, who'll pack my school bag?
-I will.

00:43:27.860 --> 00:43:30.872
-Who'll take me to school?
-I will.

00:43:31.034 --> 00:43:35.981
-What about my breakfast?
-I... what do you eat for breakfast?

00:43:36.118 --> 00:43:39.437
An omelette of 2 eggs, toast
with butter and Bournvita.

00:43:44.161 --> 00:43:48.584
A dash of coriander... and onions.
Ever had one of my omelets?

00:43:49.308 --> 00:43:52.915
-No.
-Try it today. You'll love it.

00:43:54.961 --> 00:43:58.737
-You're cutting them in such
large chunks! -That's just fine.

00:44:00.445 --> 00:44:02.293
Isn't this fun! Yes, it's fun.

00:44:03.115 --> 00:44:04.034
Now, take a look at this...

00:44:04.114 --> 00:44:07.419
a circus with one hand...
two eggs in one hand!

00:44:07.932 --> 00:44:10.070
Now take a look at how
I break both eggs using one hand.

00:44:13.979 --> 00:44:17.219
The eggs had soft-shells.
But never mind.

00:44:19.994 --> 00:44:22.070
This place is perfectly clean.

00:44:23.944 --> 00:44:26.778
What are you doing?
I'm not going to eat that!

00:44:27.108 --> 00:44:30.891
-It has shells in it. -A few
shells will make the omelette crisp.

00:44:31.608 --> 00:44:33.360
-Here go the onions...
and the chilies. -Not that way!

00:44:33.466 --> 00:44:34.188
How else?

00:44:34.268 --> 00:44:38.203
Mummy used to flip
the ingredients first.

00:44:38.339 --> 00:44:39.425
What Mummy doesn't know...

00:44:39.545 --> 00:44:42.116
...is that an omelette is an
omelette, flip or flap!

00:44:42.605 --> 00:44:45.638
Eat it and you'll know. Later
on, I'll drop you at the school.

00:44:46.019 --> 00:44:48.739
And afterwards, I'm off to
record my first song ever!

00:44:49.550 --> 00:44:52.064
Your Daddy is going to
become a famous singer.

00:44:53.900 --> 00:44:54.766
Daddy! Daddy!

00:44:54.846 --> 00:44:56.897
-What's up? -The toast is burning!
-Oh no!

00:44:57.651 --> 00:44:58.428
Oh no!

00:44:58.508 --> 00:44:59.755
Well, never mind that.

00:45:03.183 --> 00:45:04.700
Oh no!

00:45:11.673 --> 00:45:13.323
You don't know a thing!

00:45:14.457 --> 00:45:15.645
C'mon! Come on fast.

00:45:16.521 --> 00:45:19.481
Go on in... hurry. Go inside.

00:45:19.715 --> 00:45:21.721
-Who'll come to pick me up?
-I'll come.

00:45:22.191 --> 00:45:24.019
Where are you going to wait for me?

00:45:25.142 --> 00:45:27.148
I'll wait for you under this
tree, okay? Now go on inside.

00:45:28.265 --> 00:45:30.830
-What if you don't turn up?
-I said I'll come. And, I will.

00:45:31.445 --> 00:45:32.746
What if you're late?

00:45:33.438 --> 00:45:35.171
I won't be late.
I'll be here on time.

00:45:35.602 --> 00:45:37.271
What if you're still late?

00:45:40.132 --> 00:45:41.914
If I am, you can
wait under the tree.

00:45:42.234 --> 00:45:43.412
Okay? And wait for me.

00:45:43.655 --> 00:45:45.015
Go on, now. Hurry.

00:45:47.226 --> 00:45:48.197
Sunil!

00:45:48.277 --> 00:45:50.421
-When does the school get over?
-No idea.

00:45:53.334 --> 00:45:54.489
-Excuse me!
-Yes?

00:45:54.615 --> 00:45:56.450
When does the junior
school get over?

00:45:56.932 --> 00:45:59.585
-I'm that child's father.
-At 2 o'clock.

00:45:59.789 --> 00:46:01.186
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

00:46:12.023 --> 00:46:15.520
-I'm sorry to be late.
-Is this your idea of time?

00:46:16.302 --> 00:46:18.608
You've turned a star even before
you've recorded a single song.

00:46:18.981 --> 00:46:20.768
I got stuck in the traffic.

00:46:20.848 --> 00:46:23.030
Never mind.
Sit inside and get the lines.

00:46:23.199 --> 00:46:24.517
We'll record the
orchestra in the meantime

00:46:24.597 --> 00:46:26.653
-Give him his lines, will you?
-Let's have another take.

00:46:26.817 --> 00:46:28.407
Come on for the break in your life.

00:46:34.009 --> 00:46:36.728
-We can fit the 16 tracks on to 12.
-Very well. Let's try.

00:46:37.389 --> 00:46:38.741
We're ready, Mr. Pradeep.

00:46:40.744 --> 00:46:42.203
Let's have the rhythm.

00:46:42.867 --> 00:46:43.908
Silence! Silence!

00:46:45.818 --> 00:46:49.812
Still waiting here? I'm afraid
we won't be recording you today.

00:46:50.969 --> 00:46:53.255
-Sir?
-Increase the bass slightly.

00:46:53.854 --> 00:46:58.401
-When will I record?
-After a couple of days perhaps.

00:46:58.738 --> 00:47:00.296
Do keep calling to find out.

00:47:01.057 --> 00:47:02.057
Okay.

00:47:28.746 --> 00:47:31.268
I'm late by only half-an-hour.
Must you be so upset?

00:47:31.439 --> 00:47:34.878
-You said you'd be here on time.
-I did. But I was so busy.

00:47:35.767 --> 00:47:39.994
-What if someone kidnapped me?
-But no one did?

00:47:40.297 --> 00:47:41.975
What if someone did?

00:47:43.096 --> 00:47:45.808
I've told ten times that I'm sorry.

00:47:46.225 --> 00:47:48.319
You must forgive
someone who apologizes.

00:47:48.838 --> 00:47:50.074
Do you know the meaning
of the word "sorry"?

00:47:50.768 --> 00:47:52.069
Sunil! Sunil!

00:47:53.580 --> 00:47:54.923
What are you doing?

00:47:57.878 --> 00:47:58.878
What's up?

00:48:00.848 --> 00:48:05.864
This car run on batteries. It has a
horn. And, the headlights work too.

00:48:07.345 --> 00:48:11.389
-So what?
-I'll forgive you if you buy me one.

00:48:13.441 --> 00:48:15.563
What if I don't?
Won't you forgive me ever?

00:48:17.890 --> 00:48:19.951
Had it been Mummy, she
would've got the car for me.

00:48:21.666 --> 00:48:24.033
Ask your mother for one when she
comes back. Now, let's go. Come on.

00:48:28.564 --> 00:48:31.657
-250 grams of lentil... anything else?
-A packet of tea.

00:48:32.257 --> 00:48:35.140
-The Red Label, or the Yellow?
-Yellow. -Not Yellow. The Red one.

00:48:35.329 --> 00:48:37.960
-Why? -Because Mummy used
to buy the Red Label.

00:48:38.931 --> 00:48:40.031
Give me red.

