He says that I'm selfish.

01:07:54.259 --> 01:07:57.376
He asked me why I went to
see a film when he was sick.

01:07:57.883 --> 01:08:01.720
I couldn't bore myself sitting
by him all evening; now could I?

01:08:02.006 --> 01:08:03.358
Have I done anything wrong?

01:08:05.465 --> 01:08:07.534
Tell me, Anjali... have
I done anything wrong?

01:08:09.981 --> 01:08:10.942
Cut it.

01:08:11.022 --> 01:08:12.718
You were supposed to
deliver your lines.

01:08:13.124 --> 01:08:14.836
Don't you remember your lines?

01:08:18.106 --> 01:08:19.964
Will she be able to
deliver the lines?

01:08:20.274 --> 01:08:21.874
Sir, sure she'll do it.

01:08:22.269 --> 01:08:25.678
You wanted someone simple and
innocent. She'll deliver all right.

01:08:26.332 --> 01:08:28.494
Didn't I tell you that I don't
know anything about acting?

01:08:28.682 --> 01:08:30.658
Don't worry. You doing just fine.

01:08:32.187 --> 01:08:33.609
Just keep remember your line.

01:08:35.645 --> 01:08:37.082
9/3 take 4.

01:08:37.447 --> 01:08:38.002
Action!

01:08:38.082 --> 01:08:40.362
Tell me, Anjali...
What have I done wrong?

01:08:42.212 --> 01:08:45.480
You haven't done the
right thing, Deepa.

01:08:48.296 --> 01:08:50.879
D'you remember how anxious he
was when you had fallen sick?

01:08:51.837 --> 01:08:56.128
He kept by you and cared
for you like a man possessed.

01:08:56.823 --> 01:09:00.637
And you can't even
spare an evening for him!

01:09:01.849 --> 01:09:03.455
You call that boredom.

01:09:05.277 --> 01:09:09.282
The truth is that you've
never even understood Sunju.

01:09:10.183 --> 01:09:13.411
He loves you very much.

01:09:15.515 --> 01:09:16.883
Oh my God. This is too much.

01:09:17.053 --> 01:09:18.216
She's going on saying
whatever she wants to.

01:09:18.313 --> 01:09:19.317
Have you gone mad?

01:09:19.977 --> 01:09:20.977
Cut it.

01:09:21.109 --> 01:09:22.170
I'm sorry, Sir.

01:09:22.372 --> 01:09:24.547
I'd told you earlier that
I know nothing about acting.

01:09:25.036 --> 01:09:28.024
I tried it at my friend's instance.

01:09:29.560 --> 01:09:31.950
I really want to become a singer.

01:09:32.779 --> 01:09:35.252
Very well... you may sing some.

01:09:36.613 --> 01:09:37.096
Sir?!

01:09:37.176 --> 01:09:38.436
Yes, say something.

01:09:45.073 --> 01:09:57.259
"There is no regret
in life without you."

01:09:57.672 --> 01:10:04.138
"There is no regret."

01:10:30.407 --> 01:10:31.561
Please listen to
the songs I've scored.

01:10:31.712 --> 01:10:33.200
I've helped you already.

01:10:33.378 --> 01:10:36.645
I introduced you to Amar
Kaushik. And you've disgraced me.

01:10:37.146 --> 01:10:40.948
-They started misbehaving with me.
-Will they really misbehave?

01:10:42.001 --> 01:10:43.870
-You see, Mr. Gulbadan.
-You see, Mr. Rohit...

01:10:44.225 --> 01:10:46.213
I merely run a
small-time music company.

01:10:46.360 --> 01:10:48.291
We only publish
records and cassettes.

01:10:48.412 --> 01:10:51.838
I'm not a film producer.
Now, please excuse me.

01:10:57.780 --> 01:11:00.086
-I'll be back in a minute.
-Please take your time.

01:11:01.107 --> 01:11:03.319
One minute, Mr. Rohit.

01:11:04.043 --> 01:11:05.733
I can help you sell your songs.

01:11:06.220 --> 01:11:11.196
Amar Kaushik needs new tunes.
I'll get you 2000 for each tune.

01:11:11.317 --> 01:11:13.916
-Here's my card. -So they get
the credit for my compositions.

01:11:14.043 --> 01:11:15.612
Why bother about the credit?

01:11:15.822 --> 01:11:16.822
No thank you.

01:11:27.197 --> 01:11:31.170
You want me to give you a job
so you can walk out on me again.

01:11:31.500 --> 01:11:34.330
That won't happen ever again.
I beg your pardon.

01:11:35.091 --> 01:11:36.520
Please give me a chance.

01:11:36.977 --> 01:11:40.727
"Never say goodbye"

01:11:41.269 --> 01:11:45.164
"Never say goodbye"

01:11:46.023 --> 01:11:57.271
"Keep singing always."

01:12:04.739 --> 01:12:06.307
Dream of love
Beginning shot.

01:12:13.232 --> 01:12:16.055
-Isn't that, Mrs. Kiran?
-Yes. She's Rohit Kumar's wife.

01:12:16.141 --> 01:12:19.180
-She's made a heroine in films.
-She used to sing.

01:12:19.354 --> 01:12:20.908
And now, she's up
to dancing in public.

01:12:20.988 --> 01:12:23.124
Come quickly, Dad.
Take a look... over there.

01:12:24.738 --> 01:12:26.058
It's Mummy's picture.

01:12:28.054 --> 01:12:30.039
They put up the posters today.

01:12:31.458 --> 01:12:35.796
I want to see Mummy's film. You'll
take me to see it, won't you?

01:12:36.443 --> 01:12:40.666
You'll take me, won't you, Daddy?
Won't you, Daddy? Please tell me.

01:13:06.464 --> 01:13:07.526
Amar Joshi.

01:13:43.456 --> 01:13:45.502
How are we to see Mummy's film now?

01:13:47.452 --> 01:13:49.528
It's a "house-full" show.
Let's go home.

01:13:50.051 --> 01:13:56.000
I want to see Mummy's film! You'd
promised to show me Mummy's film.

01:13:56.742 --> 01:13:58.636
I want to see Mummy's film at once!

01:14:06.574 --> 01:14:07.975
Hurry up, Daddy.

01:14:28.682 --> 01:14:31.437
How come you're here?
No one is allowed up here.

01:14:31.526 --> 01:14:33.766
He wants to see how his
Mummy's film is projected.

01:14:34.040 --> 01:14:35.451
I spoke to the manager.

01:14:35.918 --> 01:14:37.593
-Is he Ms. Kiran's son?
-Yes.

01:14:37.745 --> 01:14:39.167
Very well.
You can sit here and see it.

01:14:39.679 --> 01:14:41.951
"Tell me... what
can you do for my sake"

01:14:42.398 --> 01:14:44.315
"I'd get the sun, the
moon and the stars for you."

01:14:45.501 --> 01:14:49.984
"I'd get the sun, the
moon and the stars for you."

01:14:50.800 --> 01:14:52.635
"I'd bring the heavens and earth
together for your sake."

01:14:54.150 --> 01:14:55.460
What's the matter, honey?

01:14:55.577 --> 01:14:58.056
I'd rather love a
straightforward fellow.

01:14:58.307 --> 01:15:00.787
"You needn't bring the sun,
moon, nor the stars into this."

01:15:07.032 --> 01:15:11.343
"I see love in your eyes."

01:15:11.755 --> 01:15:16.081
"I see consent in your words."

01:15:16.304 --> 01:15:18.191
"You can take your rotten son
back to America with you."

01:15:18.271 --> 01:15:20.676
"Before you leave, try
some delicious Indian cakes."

01:16:10.699 --> 01:16:12.492
Can you tell us how you are
feeling right now, Mrs. Kiran?

01:16:12.594 --> 01:16:14.348
I'm happy to see that the audiences
have liked my performance.

01:16:14.450 --> 01:16:16.426
Would you like to work
again with Paresh Kapoor?

01:16:16.506 --> 01:16:17.264
Yes, of course.

01:16:17.344 --> 01:16:20.038
Any plans for the future? What
kind of films would you like?

01:16:20.652 --> 01:16:22.165
I haven't thought about it.

01:16:22.347 --> 01:16:24.886
We hear that you are Mrs.
Kiran Kumar.

01:16:25.099 --> 01:16:28.176
-It's said that you're married,
and that you have a son. Who said that?

01:16:28.526 --> 01:16:30.259
Don't ask vulgar questions...
Please step aside.

01:16:30.339 --> 01:16:32.182
Come along, Kiran. Let's go.

01:16:34.501 --> 01:16:35.622
Mom!

01:16:37.828 --> 01:16:39.362
Mom!

01:16:58.314 --> 01:16:59.716
Mom!

01:16:59.972 --> 01:17:00.972
Please stop him.

01:17:01.357 --> 01:17:02.576
Driver stop the car.

01:17:02.921 --> 01:17:04.099
Driver don't stop.

01:17:16.519 --> 01:17:21.731
-Has Mummy forgotten me, Daddy?
-No. -Then why didn't she stop?

01:17:21.811 --> 01:17:23.557
Why didn't she talk to me?

01:17:25.830 --> 01:17:30.002
-Can I go to see her sometime?
-No. -Why not?

01:17:39.034 --> 01:17:40.349
Did you see those stars?

01:17:41.716 --> 01:17:43.973
They shine, merrily, but
they are far away from us.

01:17:45.495 --> 01:17:46.888
Your Mummy is now like a star.

01:17:48.336 --> 01:17:50.727
You can see her and long for her.

01:17:52.534 --> 01:17:54.064
But you can't go anywhere near her.

01:18:03.146 --> 01:18:04.840
Come on... Let's go home.

01:18:05.264 --> 01:18:07.251
Then, my Mummy goes to a forest.

01:18:07.545 --> 01:18:09.779
She comes across a huge
fellow in the forest.

01:18:10.371 --> 01:18:13.875
My Mummy bashes him up.

01:18:14.911 --> 01:18:17.201
-Go upstairs, Sunil.
-After a minute, please, Daddy.

01:18:17.414 --> 01:18:22.121
Then the hero comes, and
sings a song with my Mummy.

01:18:22.331 --> 01:18:26.746
-My mummy's very beautiful. -Really?
-She's more beautiful than yours.

01:18:28.865 --> 01:18:32.962
Beautiful she is. But, she's
more stubborn than she's beautiful.

01:18:33.712 --> 01:18:37.495
Why don't you go over to her,
patch up and bring her back?

01:18:38.843 --> 01:18:46.058
If I go to her now, she'll think
that I've come because she's a star.

01:18:47.543 --> 01:18:48.593
Forget her.

01:18:50.264 --> 01:18:54.018
In any case, it was she who
left me. I didn't desert her.

01:18:55.368 --> 01:19:00.691
-She can return if she wants to.
-And you're very stubborn too.

01:19:01.463 --> 01:19:03.590
We've finished the cola.

01:19:05.215 --> 01:19:06.286
Hey Moolchand!

01:19:06.570 --> 01:19:07.967
Hey Moolchand!

01:19:08.205 --> 01:19:11.249
-What's up? -2 Colas please.
-I've closed for the day.

01:19:11.422 --> 01:19:12.772
Down the shutter.

01:19:13.210 --> 01:19:17.536
-Open up if you've closed down.
-Am I to stay open all night for you?

01:19:17.724 --> 01:19:20.646
If you're so interested, you
could walk a block to fetch it.

01:19:21.058 --> 01:19:24.273
-Why don't you fetch some for us?
-Am I your servant?

01:19:24.648 --> 01:19:29.955
-Forget him. He's an illiterate.
-What?! An illiterate, am I?!

01:19:30.035 --> 01:19:31.309
Did you call me an illiterate?

01:19:31.407 --> 01:19:35.519
Oh yes. I am an illiterate. And
I know exactly what I am. Unlike you.

01:19:35.798 --> 01:19:38.793
You sing in a rotten nightclubs and
think you're no less than Elvis.

01:19:39.321 --> 01:19:42.854
He calls me an illiterate! And he
sits drinking in front of his son.

01:19:43.154 --> 01:19:47.068
You couldn't even take care of
your wife. And he is lording it over me!

01:19:47.710 --> 01:19:49.616
You bloody! What did
you say about my wife?!

01:19:49.696 --> 01:19:51.248
-No! Don't!
-What did you say about my wife?!

01:19:51.407 --> 01:19:53.396
I'll break your face! I will!

01:19:54.690 --> 01:19:57.652
-Let go! And you! Get lost!
-Don't you dare touch me!

01:19:57.800 --> 01:19:58.922
Get lost?

01:19:59.070 --> 01:20:00.667
-I will fix you.
-Go!

01:20:01.104 --> 01:20:05.480
-Let's go! Just come back here...
and I'll show you! -Don't fight!

01:20:06.819 --> 01:20:08.286
Go home, Moolchand!

01:20:09.174 --> 01:20:12.300
And you're a strange fellow. Must you
pick up a fight with such a scum?

01:20:13.027 --> 01:20:17.289
-Bad fellow! Come on, let's have
a drink. -No, he spoilt my mood.

01:20:17.674 --> 01:20:18.674
Come home, Sunil.

01:20:19.848 --> 01:20:20.848
Good night.

01:20:21.755 --> 01:20:23.953
C'mon!

01:20:24.033 --> 01:20:25.392
What's it with you, now?

01:20:25.557 --> 01:20:26.557
C'mon!

01:20:27.795 --> 01:20:30.048
Hey! I just fell down.

01:20:30.871 --> 01:20:32.318
Let's squat here for sometime.

01:20:34.662 --> 01:20:37.106
Why do you drink rum, Daddy?

01:20:39.774 --> 01:20:41.314
What did you know about rum?

01:20:41.424 --> 01:20:43.436
I know everything. Rum
is an alcoholic drink.

01:20:46.148 --> 01:20:49.653
One day, a drunk came to
the gates of our school.

01:20:49.983 --> 01:20:52.622
The kids at school were teasing
him and poking fun at him.

01:20:52.702 --> 01:20:54.738
And everyone threw stones at him.

01:20:55.008 --> 01:20:57.759
I don't want anyone to
make fun of you.

01:21:02.915 --> 01:21:04.466
Do you love me so much?

01:21:08.472 --> 01:21:09.885
I love you very much too.

01:21:11.768 --> 01:21:13.297
I love you more than
anyone else on earth.

01:21:13.394 --> 01:21:16.528
If you love me so much, you
must stop drinking.

01:21:19.718 --> 01:21:20.718
Okay!

01:21:21.460 --> 01:21:23.166
From now on, I won't drink.

01:21:23.846 --> 01:21:24.846
Okay?

01:21:26.239 --> 01:21:28.971
Hey, c'mon smile, smile.

01:21:30.062 --> 01:21:31.083
Daddy I love you.

01:21:34.903 --> 01:21:38.476
There's this fatso in our class.
Deven. He bullies everyone around.

01:21:38.920 --> 01:21:43.953
He snatched Prakash's lunch box
away. I complained to the teacher.

01:21:44.034 --> 01:21:46.872
Why complain? Box him in
the stomach. That'll do him right.

01:21:47.400 --> 01:21:49.248
-Well, what will you do to him?
-I'll box him in the stomach.

01:21:50.339 --> 01:21:51.380
C'mon now give daddy big hug.

01:22:01.107 --> 01:22:03.142
Go on now. I'll be
back to take you home.

01:22:15.571 --> 01:22:16.571
Rohit.

01:22:20.940 --> 01:22:24.133
I was passing by when
I saw the two of you.

01:22:27.826 --> 01:22:29.325
Sonu was looking quite cheerful.

01:22:35.009 --> 01:22:40.761
I'd thought I'd call
you up sometime.

01:22:42.132 --> 01:22:45.086
But I decided that it'd be
better if I met you personally.

01:22:51.087 --> 01:22:52.087
How are you?

01:22:54.976 --> 01:22:59.158
I'm fine, and I don't have much to
worry about. How have you been?

01:23:00.862 --> 01:23:06.977
Autograph please. Autograph please.

01:23:49.322 --> 01:23:50.322
Daddy!

01:23:50.591 --> 01:23:54.049
-Are you very forlorn, Daddy?
-No, I'm not. Why do you ask?

01:23:54.724 --> 01:23:58.177
Nothing particularly.
Are you thinking about Mummy?

01:24:00.930 --> 01:24:02.160
Go to sleep now.

01:24:03.354 --> 01:24:04.354
Good night.

01:24:04.678 --> 01:24:06.014
Daddy I love you.

01:24:07.014 --> 01:24:08.014
I love you too.

01:24:12.065 --> 01:24:17.698
"My heart says, go, meet him!"

01:24:17.853 --> 01:24:23.409
"I take a step;
I falter to a stop."

01:24:23.670 --> 01:24:29.304
"Sometimes my heart
reasons with me;"

01:24:29.656 --> 01:24:34.919
"sometimes I reason with my heart."

01:24:47.114 --> 01:24:52.616
"My heart says, go, meet him!"

01:24:52.871 --> 01:24:58.297
"I take a step;
I falter to a stop."

01:24:58.702 --> 01:25:04.293
"Sometimes my heart
reasons with me;"

01:25:04.537 --> 01:25:09.975
"sometimes I reason with my heart."

01:25:45.983 --> 01:25:56.913
"How long we've been separated,
my beloved!"

01:25:57.515 --> 01:26:08.658
"You look at me so and
my intentions are as nothing."

01:26:09.313 --> 01:26:19.535
"The moon's wealth lies
in the moonlight's fame."

01:26:20.083 --> 01:26:25.227
"But since losing you
it has seemed to me that

01:26:25.902 --> 01:26:30.858
if you're not here,
there's nothing else (to life)."

01:26:32.347 --> 01:26:37.700
"Do you know now how much,

01:26:37.950 --> 01:26:43.559
in my heart of hearts, I regret?"

01:26:43.792 --> 01:26:49.343
"Sometimes my heart
reasons with me;"

01:26:49.671 --> 01:26:55.143
"sometimes I reason with my heart."

01:27:45.623 --> 01:27:55.547
"How beautiful were those
days when we were together,

01:27:57.398 --> 01:28:07.426
and your arms were
within my touch."

01:28:09.051 --> 01:28:19.187
"In you, beloved, and you alone,
are my day and night."

01:28:19.883 --> 01:28:25.166
"But you are so far above me,
my dearest darling."

01:28:25.667 --> 01:28:30.976
"Now there is nothing binding us;"

01:28:31.867 --> 01:28:37.537
it's not possible to get you back."

01:28:37.697 --> 01:28:43.143
"Even thinking about it, I fret."

01:28:43.545 --> 01:28:49.167
"Sometimes my heart
reasons with me;"

01:28:49.401 --> 01:28:55.004
"sometimes I reason with my heart."

01:28:55.232 --> 01:29:00.924
"My heart says, go, meet him!"

01:29:01.218 --> 01:29:06.577
"I take a step;
I falter to a stop."

01:29:06.887 --> 01:29:12.811
"I take a step;
I falter to a stop."

01:29:25.618 --> 01:29:27.030
Mr. Kanahiya!

01:29:27.975 --> 01:29:29.407
Mr. Kanahiya!

01:29:30.133 --> 01:29:32.042
Mr. Kanahiya!

01:29:32.169 --> 01:29:33.956
-Take a look at this!
-What's up? -Read it!

01:29:34.108 --> 01:29:37.033
-Read? -Read it.. see who wrote it!
-One Pawan Malhotra.

01:29:37.115 --> 01:29:39.506
-The film director!
-Didn't he direct CHAHAT?

01:29:39.640 --> 01:29:40.761
That's him all right!

01:29:40.841 --> 01:29:43.097
He has signed me up to score the
music for his forthcoming film.

01:29:43.177 --> 01:29:46.140
-What are saying?! -Really?!
-Yes! And I can't believe it!

01:29:46.241 --> 01:29:48.995
Pawan Malhotra patted my
shoulder and said...

01:29:49.084 --> 01:29:51.351
"You're a very talented fellow!
How come I didn't meet you before?"

01:29:51.584 --> 01:29:53.855
He liked my songs very much!

01:29:53.935 --> 01:29:56.320
Thank God for that. And
congratulations!

01:29:56.708 --> 01:29:57.951
Hey Moolchand!

01:29:59.057 --> 01:30:00.725
Take a look at this! Get that?!

01:30:00.901 --> 01:30:02.079
All right. Understood.

01:30:03.557 --> 01:30:06.490
So you've got money! When
are you going to pay me up?

01:30:06.576 --> 01:30:09.242
I haven't yet received money.
I've just signed the contract.

01:30:09.381 --> 01:30:12.000
I'll get the money soon. Let's
celebrate with tea for everyone.

01:30:12.080 --> 01:30:13.881
-Very well... er... What do you mean?
-It's on me, of course.

01:30:13.961 --> 01:30:16.893
-You should've said so. Come on in.
-I'll have a cup of tea too!

01:30:17.238 --> 01:30:19.401
Sunil. Sunil, Sunil!

01:30:21.838 --> 01:30:24.603
Are you going to become
the greatest music director now?

01:30:24.897 --> 01:30:27.535
That I'll become. But, do you know
what I'm going to do before that?

01:30:27.698 --> 01:30:29.281
-What? -Your birthday is
coming up, isn't it. -Oh yes.

01:30:29.392 --> 01:30:32.017
-I'll get you a surprise gift
for your birthday. -Really?

01:30:32.113 --> 01:30:34.765
-Yes. -What's it going to be?
-How can I tell you about it now?

01:30:34.962 --> 01:30:35.902
It's surprise.

01:30:35.982 --> 01:30:38.806
I know what! Isn't it something
I showed you the other day?

01:30:39.165 --> 01:30:39.948
Well

01:30:40.028 --> 01:30:41.283
Is it yellow in color?

01:30:42.221 --> 01:30:44.535
The battery operated car!

01:30:46.833 --> 01:30:48.604
I love you my dear,
I love you.

01:30:48.902 --> 01:30:50.080
Excuse me.

01:30:50.873 --> 01:30:53.153
-Where does Mr. Rohit Kumar live?
-I'm Rohit Kumar.

01:30:58.673 --> 01:31:00.079
Ms. Kiran has sent this for you.

01:31:00.424 --> 01:31:01.424
It's Mummy's car!

01:31:01.574 --> 01:31:04.647
Hey folks! Come on quick! Take a
look at this. It's my Mummy's car!

01:31:19.223 --> 01:31:20.223
What's it?

01:31:21.539 --> 01:31:23.289
It's a letter from Kiran.

01:31:24.116 --> 01:31:28.440
She wants to celebrate Sonu's
birthday. She has invited us over.

01:31:30.285 --> 01:31:32.280
You'll go over, won't you?

01:31:37.449 --> 01:31:38.574
You should go, Rohit.

01:31:43.899 --> 01:31:46.857
Tell her that we will come. But,
there's no need to sent the car.

01:31:59.991 --> 01:32:01.026
Wow!

01:32:08.309 --> 01:32:09.934
You mustn't be naughty, Sonu.

01:32:10.594 --> 01:32:12.402
And you must speak to
everyone politely, understand?

01:32:13.237 --> 01:32:15.054
-Are you listening to me?
-Yes. Okay.

01:32:15.791 --> 01:32:17.881
If anyone offers you
anything to eat, don't be greedy.

01:32:18.536 --> 01:32:20.951
Refuse it politely. But if you must
have it, say thanks afterwards.

01:32:21.406 --> 01:32:22.500
Sonu has arrived.

01:32:24.365 --> 01:32:25.365
Sonu!

01:32:26.519 --> 01:32:27.519
Mom!

01:32:37.309 --> 01:32:38.309
Sonu!

01:32:43.786 --> 01:32:44.786
Sonu!

01:32:46.515 --> 01:32:47.791
-Hello, Kiran.
-Hi!

01:32:48.095 --> 01:32:50.533
-I hope we aren't late.
-No problem.

01:32:51.015 --> 01:32:53.433
I was worried that
you wouldn't come.

01:32:53.649 --> 01:32:54.728
But, I have come.

01:32:55.614 --> 01:32:56.614
Madam.

01:32:57.645 --> 01:32:58.098
Thank you.

01:32:58.178 --> 01:32:59.178
Kiran!

01:32:59.712 --> 01:33:01.265
Cake, cake.

01:33:03.251 --> 01:33:06.337
Happy birthday to you

01:33:06.677 --> 01:33:09.657
Happy birthday to you

01:33:09.926 --> 01:33:13.090
Happy birthday dear Sonu

01:33:13.263 --> 01:33:16.309
Happy birthday to you

01:33:24.586 --> 01:33:25.700
Wow!

01:33:47.710 --> 01:33:50.773
Let me introduce you... my wife,
Lajwanti... and... Mrs. Tolaram.

01:33:50.957 --> 01:33:52.068
Hello!

01:33:57.143 --> 01:34:00.316
You are cheating cheating.
No, no.

01:34:04.357 --> 01:34:06.292
Sorry for leaving you
alone for a while.

01:34:07.267 --> 01:34:08.678
Only a while, wasn't it?

01:34:11.551 --> 01:34:15.214
-I get childish when I'm with kids.
-You've always been childish.

01:34:15.864 --> 01:34:17.855
No Never.

01:34:19.576 --> 01:34:22.747
Sonu is still cheating at the
game. He's just like you!

01:34:26.204 --> 01:34:27.204
You're looking lovely.

01:34:28.194 --> 01:34:29.951
Oh really. Thank you.

01:34:30.606 --> 01:34:32.714
Come over here for a moment, Kiran.

01:34:33.897 --> 01:34:35.263
I'll be back in a moment.

01:34:37.535 --> 01:34:41.533
Won't you meet others around?
We have other guests too.

01:34:42.206 --> 01:34:44.923
Have you invited everyone to watch
you prancing with that fellow?

01:34:45.535 --> 01:34:49.505
I'll leave this
party if you speak so.

01:34:49.708 --> 01:34:51.834
You must consider your status.

01:34:52.261 --> 01:34:55.952
-You're a star. And, journalists
are attending. -Who invited them?

01:34:56.653 --> 01:35:00.347
I wanted to celebrate a birthday.
You've made a circus out of it.

01:35:00.475 --> 01:35:03.611
Don't teach me what to
do and what not to.

01:35:04.246 --> 01:35:05.246
Hello.

01:35:06.437 --> 01:35:09.386
As of now, just stay away from
him. We have other guests here too.

01:35:10.321 --> 01:35:13.263
-Happy tidings, Mr. Ramdayal.
-Thank you.

01:35:13.900 --> 01:35:15.350
-Happy tidings to you too.
-Thank you.

01:35:15.445 --> 01:35:17.051
-Hello. Hi.
-Excuse me.

01:35:24.360 --> 01:35:26.785
-What's up? Any problem?
-Nothing at all.

01:35:28.746 --> 01:35:30.816
They might not have taken a
liking to my presence.

01:35:35.219 --> 01:35:39.381
-I should've sent Sonu here alone.
-But why? I wanted you to come too.

01:35:39.960 --> 01:35:42.327
I wanted all of us to
celebrate Sonu's birthday together.

01:35:43.301 --> 01:35:45.448
I've taken a lot of pains
to organize this party.

01:35:45.687 --> 01:35:47.109
And now, these people...

01:35:49.056 --> 01:35:50.809
...they've spoilt my mood.

01:35:53.920 --> 01:35:54.920
It's okay.

01:35:55.944 --> 01:35:57.497
Mom! Save me.

01:35:57.984 --> 01:36:00.189
-Mom help me!
-Sonu!

01:36:00.715 --> 01:36:03.210
-I've asked you not to run around!
-Hey fatso! You won't catch me!

01:36:03.308 --> 01:36:05.623
-Let me go! He'll catch me!
-Let him.

01:36:05.743 --> 01:36:07.643
-I got caught because of you!
-That's just as well.

01:36:07.723 --> 01:36:09.456
Now you can sit
with Mummy for a while.

01:36:11.100 --> 01:36:12.100
My child!

01:36:13.284 --> 01:36:14.797
What's that mark?

01:36:15.101 --> 01:36:17.473
I was playing on the side.
And I fell down.

01:36:17.971 --> 01:36:19.737
-Oh no!
-And it bled a lot.

01:36:20.296 --> 01:36:22.905
-Did it take stitches?
-Yes 8 stitches.

01:36:23.636 --> 01:36:24.733
How did it happen?

01:36:24.976 --> 01:36:27.078
My mistake. I wasn't careful.

01:36:27.695 --> 01:36:29.939
And he didn't listen.

01:36:30.806 --> 01:36:33.607
It didn't hurt his eyes, thank God!
I could never have forgiven myself.

01:36:33.990 --> 01:36:36.293
-And I didn't even cry.
-Really?

01:36:36.373 --> 01:36:37.689
You are brave boy.

01:36:38.780 --> 01:36:40.885
-Come on, Mummy. I want to
see your house. -Let's go.

01:36:41.176 --> 01:36:43.948
-Come along too, will you?
-No. Just go on. -All right.

01:36:49.384 --> 01:36:50.340
Thank you.

01:36:50.420 --> 01:36:51.816
-See you later.
-Excuse us.

01:36:55.427 --> 01:36:56.736
-Greetings.
-Greetings.

01:36:57.782 --> 01:37:01.169
-Have you had the cakes and other
goodies? -Yes I have, thank you.

01:37:02.102 --> 01:37:04.807
-Had enough?
-Not yet. I'll have some more.

01:37:09.641 --> 01:37:13.857
-Seen the villa?
-Yes. It's a huge one.

01:37:14.415 --> 01:37:17.256
It stretches right up to the beach.

01:37:17.353 --> 01:37:19.209
-There's a swimming pool back there.
-I see!

01:37:19.577 --> 01:37:22.453
-It cost a million bucks.
-Fantastic.

01:37:22.945 --> 01:37:25.933
Are you still at
song-and-dance at the hotel?

01:37:28.496 --> 01:37:29.481
Well, you see...

01:37:29.561 --> 01:37:32.523
-Glory be to The Divine mother.
-Greetings, Mr. Gulbadan Kumar.

01:37:32.614 --> 01:37:35.556
-Greetings. -Happy tidings
on your son's birthday.

01:37:35.883 --> 01:37:40.320
I'm very upset with him, I am! Tell
me, is this any way to behave?!

01:37:40.584 --> 01:37:43.478
You're the sole object of discussion
in the film business nowadays.

01:37:44.020 --> 01:37:46.693
You are famous in
whole film industry.

01:37:46.936 --> 01:37:51.687
He has scored such lovely songs;
and he has put Amar Kaushik to shame!

01:37:52.870 --> 01:37:55.262
Well, you've become a very
important person nowadays.

01:37:55.342 --> 01:37:57.964
But you mustn't forget simple folks
like me. Do call up once in a while.

01:37:58.187 --> 01:38:03.021
-Never mind that. But you must get
me the music rights. -Sure.

01:38:03.104 --> 01:38:05.880
-Together, we'll make a stupendous
success out of it. -Surely.

01:38:05.960 --> 01:38:07.702
Divine Mother be praised!

01:38:08.571 --> 01:38:12.094
A heroine and a music
director in the family!

01:38:12.226 --> 01:38:16.234
No dearth of money! I suggest you
become a film producer. Say what?!

01:38:17.164 --> 01:38:20.050
-Excuse me.
-Oh yes. -Be back soon.

01:38:20.883 --> 01:38:25.262
-How many films have you signed?
-Just one till now.

01:38:26.500 --> 01:38:31.914
You'll get many more, I'm sure.
But take care about signing films.

01:38:32.320 --> 01:38:34.341
What'd you like to have?
Whisky or rum?

01:38:34.676 --> 01:38:35.704
I've stopped drinking.

01:38:37.186 --> 01:38:40.252
May The Divine Mother bless you!
A Coca-cola for the gentleman, please.

01:38:40.357 --> 01:38:44.803
Hello there! Nowadays, you
don't seem to care for us.

01:38:44.883 --> 01:38:48.704
That isn't the case at all.
In fact, we were discussing you.

01:38:48.784 --> 01:38:52.797
After all, he has rising star
with him. Mr. Rohit Kumar!

01:38:53.096 --> 01:38:55.758
The singer and composer.
A two-in-one!

01:38:57.766 --> 01:38:58.766
Rohit!

01:38:59.162 --> 01:39:00.162
Rohit cheers.

01:39:00.315 --> 01:39:04.631
Congratulations! So
even you've got a film!

01:39:05.707 --> 01:39:09.637
What I don't understand is
how he bagged the film.

01:39:10.957 --> 01:39:17.073
Because there still are people who
value caliber. Not names.

01:39:17.322 --> 01:39:21.866
I see! But I think that behind
every successful man lies a woman.

01:39:22.114 --> 01:39:27.572
But slightly different in this case;
a successful woman behind the man!

01:39:29.939 --> 01:39:35.657
-What do you mean? -Can a woman
who is beautiful and successful...

01:39:35.860 --> 01:39:39.964
...not do as much for her husband?
-Surely she can do!

01:39:40.044 --> 01:39:43.861
-What nonsense are you speaking?
-Do you think Pawan Malhotra has...

01:39:44.004 --> 01:39:46.080
...signed you because he
likes your rotten songs?

01:39:46.343 --> 01:39:53.439
-We were supposed to sign this film.
-You've got it because of your wife.

01:39:53.890 --> 01:39:55.490
Don't believe it, d'you?

01:39:55.681 --> 01:39:58.846
Why! It's commonplace.
Come here, Mr. Tolaram.

01:39:59.283 --> 01:40:01.903
-Come here, Mr. Tolaram.
-What's up, gentlemen?

01:40:02.317 --> 01:40:04.225
Tell him... go on! Tell him how
he has landed this film.

01:40:04.387 --> 01:40:05.372
Oh forget it!

01:40:05.452 --> 01:40:10.421
-Go on, speak up. Tell him!
-He has scored some very good songs.

01:40:10.525 --> 01:40:13.796
To hell with the songs!
You had signed us.

01:40:13.926 --> 01:40:14.926
Well yes, I did...

01:40:15.078 --> 01:40:19.627
-On his wife's say-so, you threw us
out! Correct? -Nothing of the sort!

01:40:19.832 --> 01:40:23.260
-She had merely... -D'you
hear that, Mister two-in-one?

01:40:23.340 --> 01:40:27.903
It happens dear. Everything
goes in this business.

01:40:28.395 --> 01:40:32.332
-People do use their good-looking
wives too. -Oh yes. They do.

01:40:39.585 --> 01:40:40.829
Listen!

01:40:41.108 --> 01:40:43.783
Look... look at what's going on
over there. Go on... over there.

01:40:44.105 --> 01:40:45.141
Leave me.

01:40:47.184 --> 01:40:50.689
Someone bashes me up... and you're
trying to patch up! What's going on?

01:40:51.335 --> 01:40:56.362
That's true! He couldn't
cook anything. Not even eggs!

01:40:56.489 --> 01:40:59.347
-Really?! How is it now? -Nowadays
he has picked up a few things.

01:40:59.434 --> 01:41:02.040
-He makes a dish out of potatoes
now and then. -Of potatoes?! -Yes.

01:41:02.426 --> 01:41:05.801
Sometimes, there are excess of
turmeric in it. But, I make do.

01:41:07.368 --> 01:41:08.885
Oh hello, Rohit. Come in.

01:41:09.303 --> 01:41:10.303
Go downstairs, Sunil.

01:41:10.411 --> 01:41:11.809
One minute please,
daddy, I want to tell mummy...

01:41:11.889 --> 01:41:13.401
I asked you to go downstairs!

01:41:15.571 --> 01:41:16.673
What's up, Rohit?

01:41:19.037 --> 01:41:20.449
Wait for me downstairs.

01:41:24.539 --> 01:41:26.451
Did you speak to Pawan
Malhotra about me?

01:41:27.951 --> 01:41:30.475
Did you ask him to replace me with
Amar Kaushik as a music director?

01:41:31.567 --> 01:41:33.704
-Why are you asking me this?
-Did you tell him, or, didn't you?

01:41:35.760 --> 01:41:37.162
Give me an answer, Kiran.

01:41:39.694 --> 01:41:40.694
Yes.

01:41:43.712 --> 01:41:46.263
-Why?
-Because I wanted to help you.

01:41:46.689 --> 01:41:49.366
I don't want your help!
I don't want anyone's help!

01:41:49.743 --> 01:41:53.380
-Won't I succeed without your help?
-That's not the case, Rohit.

01:41:53.460 --> 01:41:57.282
D'you want to prove that you're
so big that you can make anyone?

01:41:57.752 --> 01:42:00.778
I've never thought of it that
way, Rohit. I did it because...

01:42:00.864 --> 01:42:02.909
...I know that you can score
better music than those fellows.

01:42:03.462 --> 01:42:05.752
That's what I wanted
to prove on my own.

01:42:06.616 --> 01:42:08.195
And now, you've spoiled everything.

01:42:09.348 --> 01:42:12.556
People will say that I've succeeded
because my wife helped me.

01:42:13.165 --> 01:42:14.998
My success will never be mine!

01:42:17.251 --> 01:42:21.254
-I can't do it! -Tell Pawan
Malhotra that I won't do this film!

01:42:21.337 --> 01:42:24.474
Don't lose your head, Rohit.
Pawan Malhotra liked your music.

01:42:24.717 --> 01:42:27.726
That's why he has signed you.
I haven't forced him to.

01:42:28.610 --> 01:42:31.510
What does it matter if a few
people tell you a lot of nonsense?

01:42:32.546 --> 01:42:36.111
I'm your wife. If I don't
help you, who else will?

01:42:37.502 --> 01:42:40.667
I see! So can you walk out on me,
or come to my aid at your sweet will?

01:42:41.592 --> 01:42:45.860
You don't want to help me. You just
want to show off your magnanimity.

01:42:46.060 --> 01:42:47.502
You want to show me how
small I am, compared to you.

01:42:47.701 --> 01:42:50.043
And you want to show your concern
for me though you live apart.

01:42:58.028 --> 01:43:01.743
You've always thought ill of me.
You've always got me wrong.

01:43:01.823 --> 01:43:03.321
Why must I try to understand
you in the first place?

01:43:04.424 --> 01:43:06.828
I don't want to understand you.
Nor do I want to see you ever!

01:43:06.945 --> 01:43:08.729
Don't ever try to meet me again!

01:43:10.760 --> 01:43:13.852
Stop! Rohit!

01:43:15.289 --> 01:43:17.772
-Don't step inside this house ever!
-Listen to me! Please!

01:43:17.940 --> 01:43:22.012
Come to your senses!

01:43:36.540 --> 01:43:37.942
How did all this come here?

01:43:38.265 --> 01:43:41.327
Look, Daddy! My birthday
presents! Mummy sent these over.

01:43:43.752 --> 01:43:47.610
This is a military jeep. It
turns around whenever it collides.

01:43:49.318 --> 01:43:51.857
Look! Here's a remote control car.

01:43:55.710 --> 01:43:58.998
Why can't we live in Mummy's house?

01:44:01.742 --> 01:44:03.289
Don't you like this house?

01:44:03.917 --> 01:44:06.410
-This home is fine, but...
-What of it?

01:44:06.919 --> 01:44:09.620
But her house is so
big... and it's so nice.

01:44:10.018 --> 01:44:13.839
She has 3 TV sets.
We don't have a single one.

01:44:20.688 --> 01:44:22.683
What did Mummy tell you
at this party yesterday?

01:44:23.821 --> 01:44:26.387
She said that she
loves me very much.

01:44:27.561 --> 01:44:28.758
What did you tell her?

01:44:29.193 --> 01:44:32.332
That she's the best Mummy on earth.

01:44:35.746 --> 01:44:38.255
So now you want to
live with Mummy, do you?

01:44:42.660 --> 01:44:45.215
-I'm asking you something.
-Do you know something?

01:44:45.459 --> 01:44:48.726
Mummy is going to buy the
battery-operated car for me.

01:44:49.164 --> 01:44:53.137
-Did you ask her for it?
-No, I just told her that I like it.

01:44:53.274 --> 01:44:55.771
She said that she'd buy it for me.

01:44:56.013 --> 01:44:58.787
Why did you have to ask her for it?
I was supposed to buy it for you.

01:45:00.144 --> 01:45:04.539
-You haven't got it yet.
-But I was to get it for your birthday.

01:45:05.009 --> 01:45:07.400
-And now, my birthday is gone.
-All right. I know that.

01:45:10.935 --> 01:45:13.241
I'll get you that car today.

01:45:14.541 --> 01:45:15.927
-Promise?
-Promise.

01:45:16.104 --> 01:45:17.988
Understood? I'll get
it today! For you.

01:45:18.136 --> 01:45:19.918
My car is coming today!

01:45:32.188 --> 01:45:36.965
-How much does that car cost?
-5000 Rupees. -5000?! -Yes.

01:45:37.967 --> 01:45:41.185
-It's a bit too much for that car.
-Fixed price. Take it or leave it.

01:45:42.286 --> 01:45:45.095
-An advance of 5000 Rupees?!
-I need the money, Sir.

01:45:45.623 --> 01:45:50.192
So you need all of 5000 Rupees!
D'you hear that, Mr. Godwill?

01:45:51.329 --> 01:45:53.296
You may deduct a thousand rupees
every month out of my salary.

01:45:53.478 --> 01:45:57.029
-It'd be adjusted within 5 months.
-Will you be here for 5 months?

01:45:57.685 --> 01:46:00.645
Seems like you've got a chance
to sing in some third rate film.

01:46:00.774 --> 01:46:02.499
And now, you're looking for
chance to give me the slip.

01:46:02.594 --> 01:46:03.686
No, Sir.

01:46:04.893 --> 01:46:07.154
That isn't the case at all!
I've forgotten these dreams.

01:46:07.717 --> 01:46:11.334
The only person I have to
myself is my 6 year old son.

01:46:13.043 --> 01:46:17.263
Yesterday was his birthday.
And I had promised him a gift.

01:46:17.687 --> 01:46:20.263
A gift... worth 5000 bucks!

01:46:23.382 --> 01:46:27.229
D'you hear that. Mr. Godwill?! I've
never given a single gift to my son.

01:46:27.351 --> 01:46:29.923
And my good man wants to give a
gift worth 5000 bucks to his son!

01:46:32.768 --> 01:46:39.012
You've spun a good spiel. But, I'm
not one to be taken in my your story.

01:46:39.281 --> 01:46:42.525
-Please try to understand...
-Don't waste my time. And back to work!

01:46:44.726 --> 01:46:47.399
Let's get working. We don't have
a circus happening here, do we?

01:46:51.126 --> 01:46:53.431
-So you won't let me have the
money will you? -Not at all.

01:46:56.579 --> 01:46:59.500
What are you doing?! I'll call
the police! Stop him, Godwill!

01:47:00.001 --> 01:47:01.485
What hooliganism is this?

01:47:01.886 --> 01:47:04.607
Waiter, waiter, waiter look.

01:47:04.694 --> 01:47:05.694
Put it down on my account.

01:47:07.138 --> 01:47:08.138
Stop him!

01:47:11.049 --> 01:47:12.110
Catch him!

01:47:24.354 --> 01:47:26.837
Snatch the money from him!

01:47:47.303 --> 01:47:50.963
Know something, aunt Farida? Daddy
is getting me a battery-powered car.

01:47:51.319 --> 01:47:53.345
Is that so? That's
good news, I say.

01:47:54.352 --> 01:47:56.632
It's getting late.
Time to have dinner.

01:47:57.601 --> 01:48:00.268
I won't eat now.
I'll eat when Daddy comes home.

01:48:00.413 --> 01:48:01.526
No knowing when he'll return.

01:48:01.824 --> 01:48:03.525
I must go home and get my
kids to do their homework.

01:48:03.786 --> 01:48:06.853
-Go on... eat your dinner quickly.
-No. I won't eat now.

01:48:07.976 --> 01:48:10.753
Very well. I'm leaving the food
here. Eat it when you feel hungry.

01:49:01.068 --> 01:49:02.068
Daddy!

01:49:04.361 --> 01:49:07.091
When did you return?
I didn't even get to know!

01:49:13.009 --> 01:49:14.766
Where's the car, Daddy?

01:49:16.394 --> 01:49:20.754
-Why haven't you eaten yet?
-I was waiting for you.

01:49:21.994 --> 01:49:25.480
You mustn't stay awake so
late. I don't like this at all.

01:49:26.122 --> 01:49:30.327
I was waiting so we
could eat together.

01:49:49.713 --> 01:49:50.713
I'm sorry Sonu.

01:49:51.789 --> 01:49:52.789
I'm sorry.

01:49:53.508 --> 01:49:58.279
-What's happened, Daddy?
-I lost my son. I have lost.

01:50:00.391 --> 01:50:01.661
Don't cry.

01:50:02.555 --> 01:50:07.327
-Please don't cry, Daddy.
-My son asked me for only one thing.

01:50:08.293 --> 01:50:09.817
And I couldn't get it for him.

01:50:12.869 --> 01:50:14.558
This is the worst
defeat in my life.

01:50:16.510 --> 01:50:19.628
I don't want that car, Daddy.
Really... I don't want it.

01:50:23.547 --> 01:50:25.335
No, no.

01:50:37.771 --> 01:50:42.705
Here... I have some money.
And I'm going to get more.

01:50:44.724 --> 01:50:48.192
And I'm going to
get that car for you.

01:50:49.528 --> 01:50:50.413
I love you.

01:50:50.493 --> 01:50:51.686
I love you to Daddy.

01:50:52.758 --> 01:50:55.576
But, please stop
drinking, Daddy. Please.

01:50:59.154 --> 01:51:06.071
I'll get that car
for you, Sonu. I will.

01:51:07.271 --> 01:51:09.880
Sonu.. I love you, Sonu.

01:51:11.373 --> 01:51:12.884
I love you.

01:51:34.405 --> 01:51:35.405
-Excuse me.
-Yes, sir.

01:51:35.502 --> 01:51:37.938
-Mr. Pawan Malhotra has summoned
me here. -Please follow me.

01:51:45.742 --> 01:51:49.153
Please forgive me, Rohit. I've had
you summoned here using the alias.

01:51:50.682 --> 01:51:52.165
Else, you wouldn't have come.

01:51:52.838 --> 01:51:54.412
I want to discuss something.

01:51:55.852 --> 01:51:57.388
Is anything worth discussing?

01:51:57.838 --> 01:51:59.889
Please sit down, Rohit.

01:52:06.165 --> 01:52:09.735
You had told me something the other
day. All I want to know is whether...

01:52:12.063 --> 01:52:14.722
...it is your final decision.
-Why?

01:52:15.586 --> 01:52:17.985
Are you still firm about
not meeting me ever again?

01:52:20.638 --> 01:52:21.638
Absolutely.

01:52:24.416 --> 01:52:28.808
-In that ease, I want my son.
-What was it you said?!

01:52:29.660 --> 01:52:34.004
-I want Sonu to live with me.
-You want Sonu! Incredible!

01:52:34.259 --> 01:52:38.186
How could you even think of it?
You left him when he needed you.

01:52:38.551 --> 01:52:41.060
-D'you want me to... -You haven't
seen him in a year and a half.

01:52:41.263 --> 01:52:44.292
You haven't even asked if he's dead
or alive. And now you want him!

01:52:44.746 --> 01:52:46.508
Sonu needs me.

01:52:46.818 --> 01:52:48.983
-He'll be happy with me.
-And, isn't he happy with me?

01:52:49.825 --> 01:52:53.622
Now wait a minute! D'you mean to
say that I can't keep him happy?

01:52:53.744 --> 01:52:57.123
-I didn't say so. -D'you think
you can give him more happiness...

01:52:57.248 --> 01:52:59.748
...because you're wealthy?

01:52:59.894 --> 01:53:01.455
-Please don't shout, Rohit.
-Why mustn't I!

01:53:01.601 --> 01:53:03.201
I don't care for your society.

01:53:03.797 --> 01:53:07.612
I'm his mother.
And you can't deny my right.

01:53:07.803 --> 01:53:09.339
Neither can you mine!

01:53:09.916 --> 01:53:12.398
I'm his father.
And he stays with me.

01:53:15.262 --> 01:53:17.400
I'd even go to court to get Sonu.

01:53:29.572 --> 01:53:31.839
Well, how do I play that?
Just like Daddy, don't I?

01:53:40.803 --> 01:53:43.132
I'm sorry for having
touched the piano, Daddy.

01:53:54.227 --> 01:53:57.300
In terms of this notice, Ms.
Kiran seeks a divorce from you.

01:53:57.965 --> 01:54:00.285
And, she wants that the child
be placed in her custody.

01:54:03.139 --> 01:54:04.334
All I want is my son.

01:54:05.114 --> 01:54:10.243
I'll tell you something
before I take the case.

01:54:10.745 --> 01:54:14.027
In such cases, the decision
generally favors the mother.

01:54:14.232 --> 01:54:16.371
I have been parenting him
for nearly two years now.

01:54:16.566 --> 01:54:19.502
-She had abandoned the child.
-Yet, Ms. Kiran remains the mother.

01:54:20.082 --> 01:54:22.814
Besides, she's a successful woman.
You don't have a job. That's worse.

01:54:22.984 --> 01:54:23.971
-Sir.
-Yes.

01:54:24.051 --> 01:54:25.250
Mane sir has send file.

01:54:26.184 --> 01:54:27.605
Here is no signature
Go and get signature.

01:54:27.745 --> 01:54:29.414
-And give that file also.
-Yes sir.

01:54:29.592 --> 01:54:35.966
You'd have to pay for court fees and
mine to the extent of 50 or 60,000.

01:54:36.402 --> 01:54:39.786
That's irrespective of whether you
win or lose. D'you have the money?

01:54:42.989 --> 01:54:47.224
-Yes. Please prepare the brief.
-Very well.

01:54:47.547 --> 01:54:50.974
You may come here on Wednesday
at 10 am. We'll discuss the case.

01:54:51.327 --> 01:54:55.027
Please bring 20,000 towards
expenses in advance All right.

01:54:57.613 --> 01:54:58.613
Yes.

01:55:06.034 --> 01:55:08.897
I can pay 15,000 for
all these instruments.

01:55:09.043 --> 01:55:10.883
15000 only! How come?!

01:55:11.220 --> 01:55:14.089
The piano is worth at least
20,000. I'd bought it for 30,000.

01:55:14.687 --> 01:55:17.007
I should get at least 40,000
for all the instruments.

01:55:17.286 --> 01:55:20.121
This is business for me. I should
be able to earn a bit out of this.

01:55:22.648 --> 01:55:28.158
-Well, give me at least 25,000.
-I can't pay more than 15,000.

01:55:28.238 --> 01:55:30.685
-Very well, you may leave.
-You seem to be cross with me, Sir.

01:55:30.765 --> 01:55:33.456
We don't want to sell.
Now, please leave.

01:55:33.564 --> 01:55:34.907
It's yours, do as you please.

01:55:34.987 --> 01:55:36.554
-Please leave.
-Excuse me, gentleman.

01:55:36.942 --> 01:55:39.995
What a waste of time!
Why did they call me at all?

01:55:41.352 --> 01:55:44.747
Have you gone out of your mind?
Can a junk dealer appreciate these?

01:55:45.693 --> 01:55:49.958
You're worrying for nothing. Sell
my furniture to raise the money.

01:55:53.044 --> 01:55:56.527
No. You've already
done so much for me.

01:55:58.640 --> 01:56:00.947
-I'll sell my songs.
-Sell your songs?!

01:56:01.283 --> 01:56:03.835
-To whom?
-To Amar Kaushik.

01:56:04.050 --> 01:56:05.916
You've really gone
out of your mind.

01:56:07.395 --> 01:56:09.718
He's willing to pay
me 1000 for every song.

01:56:10.068 --> 01:56:11.407
Who gets the credit?

01:56:12.123 --> 01:56:15.634
-They get the credits.
-You mustn't do such a thing.

01:56:16.569 --> 01:56:20.038
These are fruits of your labor.
They're your hopes, your dreams.

01:56:21.272 --> 01:56:23.449
How can you give
that away to someone?

01:56:25.529 --> 01:56:30.008
Your songs are beautiful, Rohit.
You must get credit for these songs.

01:56:31.952 --> 01:56:34.687
That's what I thought too.
I thought my songs were beautiful.

01:56:35.893 --> 01:56:39.164
But, I've tried for so many years.
And, no one seems to like them.

01:56:40.209 --> 01:56:42.097
And, at long last, I think
I have been entirely wrong.

01:56:42.389 --> 01:56:44.814
-My songs might really be worthless.
-I don't agree to that.

01:56:45.245 --> 01:56:51.202
-You're making a big mistake, Rohit.
-I may be. But, if in exchange...

01:56:51.621 --> 01:56:56.800
...for these, I can have Sonu,
then these songs are priceless.

01:56:59.075 --> 01:57:01.011
Else, these are no more
than scribbling on paper.

01:57:25.298 --> 01:57:28.113
"Why did you break my heart?"

01:57:29.495 --> 01:57:32.171
"Why did you fallen in love?"

01:57:33.693 --> 01:57:38.885
"Why did you go away.
Away away away away."

01:57:39.735 --> 01:57:43.411
"Why did you steal my heart"

01:57:43.834 --> 01:57:47.582
"when you had to break it?"

01:57:48.148 --> 01:57:51.679
"Why did you fall in love with me"

01:57:52.268 --> 01:57:56.266
"when you had to spurn me?"

01:57:56.488 --> 01:57:59.759
"Why did you steal my heart"

01:58:00.612 --> 01:58:04.124
"when you had to break it?"

01:58:04.840 --> 01:58:08.443
"Why did you fall in love with me"

01:58:09.046 --> 01:58:13.046
"when you had to spurn me?"

01:58:13.457 --> 01:58:16.390
"Why did you break my heart?"

01:58:17.628 --> 01:58:20.599
"Why did you fallen in love?"

01:58:21.814 --> 01:58:26.985
"Why did you go away.
Away away away away."

01:58:44.081 --> 01:58:48.680
"You taught my heart how to beat;"

01:58:49.063 --> 01:58:52.841
"you taught my heart
how to writhe in pain."

01:58:53.178 --> 01:58:57.172
"Somehow tears stayed
hidden in my eyes;"

01:58:57.447 --> 01:59:01.596
"you taught them how to brim over."

01:59:07.495 --> 01:59:10.960
"Why did you settle into my breast"

01:59:11.804 --> 01:59:15.419
"when you had to
toy with my heart?"

01:59:16.041 --> 01:59:19.512
"Why did you fall in love with me"

01:59:20.207 --> 01:59:24.262
"when you had to spurn me?"

01:59:24.423 --> 01:59:28.394
"Why did you steal my heart?"

01:59:28.845 --> 01:59:31.738
"Why did you break my heart?""

01:59:32.988 --> 01:59:35.776
"Why did you fallen in love?"

01:59:37.138 --> 01:59:42.447
"Why did you go away.
Away away away away."

02:00:03.592 --> 02:00:08.235
"Whenever our gazes met,"

02:00:08.661 --> 02:00:12.544
"it was like flames
rose from my heart."

02:00:12.762 --> 02:00:16.721
"From my breath something
drifted out like smoke;"

02:00:17.005 --> 02:00:21.097
"it was made from me,
neither living nor dying."

02:00:27.202 --> 02:00:30.884
"Why did you set me on fire when"

02:00:31.146 --> 02:00:34.857
"you'd have to extinguish
and forsake my heart?"

02:00:35.529 --> 02:00:39.292
"Why did you fall in love with me"

02:00:39.661 --> 02:00:43.828
"when you'd have to spurn me?"

02:00:43.983 --> 02:00:47.784
The filmfare award for the Best
music director, this year for...

02:00:48.033 --> 02:00:54.316
...the song DIL MERA CHURAYA
KYON goes to Amar Kaushik.

02:01:43.479 --> 02:01:45.277
Yes, Mr. Bhokwani.
You may proceed.

02:01:45.388 --> 02:01:49.478
Mr. Rohit Kumar's attorney
has sent me this letter today.

02:01:50.074 --> 02:01:54.414
He has agreed to divorce Ms. Kiran.

02:01:54.908 --> 02:01:58.800
But he has refused the prayer to
place Ms. Kiran's son Sunil Kumar...

02:01:58.880 --> 02:02:01.637
...under her custody.

02:02:02.649 --> 02:02:05.381
The case therefore rests
upon the contention...

02:02:05.584 --> 02:02:07.308
...as to who may have custody of
the child.

02:02:08.101 --> 02:02:10.736
Before arguing the case
I'll present some witnesses.

02:02:11.283 --> 02:02:12.870
This lawyer is a tough one.

02:02:13.946 --> 02:02:17.298
I shall speak the truth,
and nothing but the truth.

02:02:17.437 --> 02:02:22.089
Can you tell the court something
about your daughter, Mrs. Ramdayal?

02:02:22.992 --> 02:02:25.720
My daughter is a simple girl, and
has all the qualities of a girl...

02:02:26.190 --> 02:02:32.270
...who has had a respectable
upbringing. She's an obedient girl.

02:02:32.711 --> 02:02:35.921
Why then, did she marry Rohit
Kumar against your wishes?

02:02:37.090 --> 02:02:40.568
That's the only mistake she
has committed in all her life.

02:02:41.828 --> 02:02:44.534
And, she's still
suffering for her mistake.

02:02:47.580 --> 02:02:50.338
This man had treated
her so cruelly that...

02:02:51.307 --> 02:02:54.161
...she was forced to leave
his house at midnight.

02:02:55.953 --> 02:02:57.816
Thank you Mrs. Ramdayal.
You may step down.

02:02:58.755 --> 02:03:03.067
Can you tell the court about Rohit
Kumar's character, Mr. Ramdayal?

02:03:03.676 --> 02:03:07.722
What can I say about a
man who has no character?

02:03:08.418 --> 02:03:12.443
He's a scoundrel; and he's wayward.
You mustn't consider his appearance.

02:03:12.903 --> 02:03:15.505
He inveigled my daughter using
those looks, and with his words.

02:03:15.819 --> 02:03:18.115
-Really?! -He claimed to be
a singer of great caliber.

02:03:18.570 --> 02:03:20.309
And he said that he was going to
become a famous music director.

02:03:20.645 --> 02:03:22.963
He's still where he was.
And look at my daughter!

02:03:23.059 --> 02:03:25.789
She came out, and now, she's so
successful. And we don't want...

02:03:25.891 --> 02:03:28.577
...Sonu to live with him,
because the boy will turn wayward.

02:03:29.109 --> 02:03:30.391
Thank you,
Mr. Ramdayal.

02:03:33.796 --> 02:03:37.732
Has Rohit Kumar ever shied away
from fulfilling his responsibilities?

02:03:38.075 --> 02:03:40.744
-No. -Has he ever tried to
shirk responsibility? -No.

02:03:40.972 --> 02:03:44.805
-Has he been negligent
towards his son? -Never.

02:03:45.457 --> 02:03:47.977
In fact, he spends
most of his time with his son.

02:03:48.396 --> 02:03:51.912
He plays with the boy;
amuses him;...

02:03:52.149 --> 02:03:57.029
...reads stories to him and takes
him outdoors. Sunil is his very life.

02:03:58.860 --> 02:04:02.851
I've seen very few fathers who
would do as much for their children.

02:04:04.683 --> 02:04:06.201
Thank you very much, Mrs. Farida.

02:04:06.303 --> 02:04:08.334
That's all your honour.
Your witness Mr. Bhojwani.

02:04:12.206 --> 02:04:13.206
Farida.

02:04:13.842 --> 02:04:16.304
For how many years
have you known Mrs. Kiran?

02:04:16.767 --> 02:04:18.049
Some 7 years now.

02:04:18.261 --> 02:04:19.261
Good.

02:04:19.458 --> 02:04:23.759
Has Ms. Kiran ever told
you about her personal life?

02:04:23.842 --> 02:04:24.842
I objection mylord.

02:04:25.039 --> 02:04:28.518
Questions about Ms. Kiran's personal
life may be addressed to her only.

02:04:28.615 --> 02:04:29.615
Overruled

02:04:30.530 --> 02:04:33.103
Did she tell you anything about
her personal life.

02:04:34.340 --> 02:04:35.622
-Yes. -What?

02:04:39.264 --> 02:04:42.557
-She was unhappy.
-With whom was she unhappy?

02:04:44.708 --> 02:04:48.946
-She was unhappy about Rohit.
-Did Ms. Kiran ever tell you...

02:04:49.026 --> 02:04:52.246
...that Rohit Kumar doesn't
care about his son at all?

02:04:59.033 --> 02:05:01.206
Please reply, Ms. Farida.
I haven't yet heard you.

02:05:03.143 --> 02:05:05.081
Yes. But, that had
happened before Kiran left.

02:05:05.172 --> 02:05:06.545
Maybe. But he...

02:05:06.649 --> 02:05:10.823
...didn't care about his son at all.
Now, Ms. Farida, can you tell me...

02:05:11.216 --> 02:05:17.168
...if you ever advised Ms. Kiran
to break away? -No. I did not.

02:05:19.941 --> 02:05:23.570
3 days before she walked out,
did you not tell her that:

02:05:23.902 --> 02:05:29.000
"If you are so unhappy, it'd
be better for you to leave"?

02:05:29.901 --> 02:05:32.142
Yes. But I never thought that she'd
really do something like that.

02:05:32.272 --> 02:05:38.424
"If you are so unhappy, it'd be
better for you to leave Rohit"

02:05:38.802 --> 02:05:43.195
Kiran was a good friend. And, I was
concerned about her. I still am.

02:05:43.612 --> 02:05:48.738
-And whatever I told her...
-Was born out of your feeling that...

02:05:48.887 --> 02:05:52.503
...had Kiran lived on with Rohit,
she would've gone mad or could've...

02:05:52.768 --> 02:05:57.354
...had a nervous breakdown, or she
may have even been driven to suicide.

02:05:57.741 --> 02:06:01.475
-But I... -D'you want an innocent
child to live with such a man!

02:06:01.615 --> 02:06:02.615
That's all milord.

02:06:04.756 --> 02:06:08.511
You're making a big mistake, Kiran.
Rohit has changed completely.

02:06:08.734 --> 02:06:09.588
Order order.

02:06:09.668 --> 02:06:12.543
He is no more what he used to
be. Listen to me, Kiran. Please!

02:06:13.125 --> 02:06:18.597
Don't take Sonu away from Rohit.
He needs Sunil. Without him...

02:06:19.092 --> 02:06:21.269
-Order, order please!
-Please don't do this to him.

02:06:22.195 --> 02:06:25.011
If you do not step down, it will be
regarded as a contempt of this court.

02:06:31.083 --> 02:06:33.201
I can't quite understand how you're
going about this case, Mr. Bhatija.

02:06:33.445 --> 02:06:35.628
At this rate, we're going to
lose... out of the way, please.

02:06:36.222 --> 02:06:39.347
Our witnesses are saying the truth.
And her lawyer is twisting facts.

02:06:39.636 --> 02:06:44.431
D'you want me to tell lies too?
Must I stoop to Bhojwani's level?

02:06:45.330 --> 02:06:48.311
D'you want me to raise a stink
over Ms. Kiran's personal life?

02:06:48.774 --> 02:06:52.093
Am I to prove that she's deranged?
Must I accuse her of adultery?

02:06:52.332 --> 02:06:54.430
-But that isn't true!
-Are you concerned about the truth?

02:06:54.510 --> 02:06:57.526
Or, do you want your son? Tell me.
I'll handle the case accordingly.

02:06:57.667 --> 02:07:00.263
I can present false witnesses as
he does. Do you want me to do that?

02:07:02.491 --> 02:07:06.060
No. Do it honestly.

02:07:07.037 --> 02:07:08.037
I'm sorry.

02:07:12.003 --> 02:07:17.993
Look at her now. She has done well
for herself. She's the ideal woman.

02:07:18.309 --> 02:07:19.779
She is the ultimate woman.

02:07:20.039 --> 02:07:21.068
Thank you.

02:07:21.265 --> 02:07:22.287
Mr. Bhatiga.

02:07:22.771 --> 02:07:23.898
No question.

02:07:25.464 --> 02:07:26.464
My lord.

02:07:26.839 --> 02:07:30.363
My next witness is
Mr. Moolchand Gangar.

02:07:34.748 --> 02:07:36.920
-Where did he transpire from?
-I have no idea.

02:07:37.377 --> 02:07:39.702
-Who is he?
-The grocer in my neighborhood.

02:07:40.682 --> 02:07:43.710
-We don't get along too well.
-You haven't told me about him.

02:07:45.148 --> 02:07:48.994
-Is your shop located under
Rohit Kumar's residence? -Exactly.

02:07:49.231 --> 02:07:51.439
In that case, you might be
knowing Rohit well.

02:07:52.050 --> 02:07:52.954
Very well indeed.

02:07:53.034 --> 02:07:57.413
-I've heard that he buys groceries
from your shop on credit. -Always.

02:07:57.643 --> 02:08:01.225
-He might also be settling
your dues. -No. -Doesn't he?!

02:08:01.448 --> 02:08:03.910
Why then do you still
let him enjoy your credit?

02:08:04.044 --> 02:08:07.110
I allow credits to everyone. You
buy from me and you get credit.

02:08:08.508 --> 02:08:11.813
Did you threaten to lodge a
complaint with the police, when...

02:08:11.893 --> 02:08:15.205
...he had gotten
drunk and beaten you up?

02:08:19.923 --> 02:08:24.475
If I told tales about your wife,
you would've bashed are up too.

02:08:24.770 --> 02:08:27.152
Does it mean that
you aren't a good man?

02:08:27.294 --> 02:08:31.172
It's not a question of being good
or bad. It's more a matter of intent.

02:08:31.623 --> 02:08:35.751
-Now, did he pay you up after
the incident? -No, he didn't.

02:08:35.965 --> 02:08:38.798
Now how does a man run his
household under the circumstances?

02:08:39.180 --> 02:08:40.572
How can such a person
look after his son?

02:08:40.770 --> 02:08:41.902
You mean his son, Sunil?

02:08:42.045 --> 02:08:46.414
-Yes. -He'd give his life for Sunil.
He loves his son very much.

02:08:46.494 --> 02:08:48.994
He loves his son more than
I can ever love my son.

02:08:49.074 --> 02:08:51.793
Love can't satiate hunger.

02:08:53.033 --> 02:08:56.919
And what can one who has wrecked
his home provide for his son?

02:08:57.078 --> 02:08:58.859
Rohit Kumar has not
wrecked his own family.

02:08:58.939 --> 02:09:03.472
It's she... that woman sitting over
there? She has wrecked the family!

02:09:04.591 --> 02:09:07.209
Please answer questions put to
you. Do not try to give a verdict.

02:09:07.357 --> 02:09:11.582
Forgive me if I have erred. This is
my first ever appearance in court.

02:09:11.943 --> 02:09:14.450
-I came here because he summoned me.
-You may leave now.

02:09:14.735 --> 02:09:18.442
What you say is true. I've hated
Rohit Kumar for not repaying me.

02:09:18.522 --> 02:09:20.861
I've even quarreled
with him for my money.

02:09:21.104 --> 02:09:24.164
But my money isn't the bone of
contention. This is about his son.

02:09:24.244 --> 02:09:29.513
You asked me what he'd do for his
son. Well, he has sold himself!

02:09:29.981 --> 02:09:33.515
It might be easy for Ms. Kiran
to foot the bill for this lawsuit.

02:09:33.673 --> 02:09:35.693
She's a famous heroine.
And she has loads of money.

02:09:35.922 --> 02:09:40.797
But, it wasn't easy for Rohit. Do
you know what he did for his son?

02:09:41.310 --> 02:09:46.666
He sold his life's savings...
his music... to Amar Kaushik.

02:09:47.046 --> 02:09:49.368
They are now taking
credit for his music.

02:09:53.648 --> 02:09:57.741
-Rohit Kumar must've told you that.
-No he didn't. But I know better.

02:09:57.932 --> 02:10:01.293
I've heard all his songs so often,
it's still coming out of my ears.

02:10:01.509 --> 02:10:06.133
The song "RAJ A KO RANI SE
PYAR HO GAYA"...it's Rohit's.

02:10:07.063 --> 02:10:11.997
I'm telling you the truth! The song
wasn't written by Amar Kaushik.

02:10:16.737 --> 02:10:17.737
Mrs. Kiran.

02:10:18.197 --> 02:10:22.614
-Do you love your son?
-Yes. I love him dearly.

02:10:22.786 --> 02:10:25.537
Why did you leave him?

02:10:26.631 --> 02:10:35.047
He used to think that I'll remain
a failure. It ruined my confidence.

02:10:37.328 --> 02:10:42.485
I became fatalistic
about my failures.

02:10:44.195 --> 02:10:47.804
I was confused, and
I started losing my confidence.

02:10:50.438 --> 02:10:54.466
I felt stifled and confused.
I was scared. And I left my home.

02:10:56.345 --> 02:11:06.502
Then, I'd thought it better for
Sunil's sake not to take him along.

02:11:06.809 --> 02:11:10.762
Why then do you seek
custody of your son now?

02:11:11.647 --> 02:11:23.401
I know I had deserted him. I can
never forgive myself for the mistake.

02:11:27.586 --> 02:11:33.445
But, the situation has changed.
And, I am confident of myself.

02:11:35.938 --> 02:11:41.877
I can look after Sonu very well.
After all I reared him for 5 years.

02:11:43.479 --> 02:11:46.356
Must my child be taken away from me
because I've been away for 2 years?

02:11:50.635 --> 02:11:51.935
He needs me now.

02:11:56.070 --> 02:11:59.384
But I don't say that he
doesn't need his father.

02:12:00.595 --> 02:12:05.367
But, he's still a child. He needs a
mother more than he needs a father.

02:12:08.423 --> 02:12:09.635
And, I'm his mother.

02:12:13.574 --> 02:12:15.275
I'm his mother!

02:12:22.942 --> 02:12:23.942
Thank you.

02:12:24.532 --> 02:12:25.532
That's all.

02:12:26.852 --> 02:12:27.852
Mrs. Kiran.

02:12:28.058 --> 02:12:30.742
You've spent nearly 6
years with your husband.

02:12:31.389 --> 02:12:35.021
-Has he ever manhandled you?
-No. He hasn't.

02:12:35.361 --> 02:12:37.133
-Did he use abusive language?
-No.

02:12:37.362 --> 02:12:38.986
Has he ever ill-treated your son?

02:12:40.218 --> 02:12:41.062
No.

02:12:41.142 --> 02:12:43.866
-Do you regard your husband
to be a drunkard? -No.

02:12:44.236 --> 02:12:47.891
Has he ever had relations with other
women... in the nature of infidelity?

02:12:49.636 --> 02:12:54.774
-No. -Then, the reason for your
desertion becomes amply clear.

02:12:56.165 --> 02:13:02.753
With whom did you have the longest
lasting relationship before marriage?

02:13:04.308 --> 02:13:07.843
-With my parents. -And you spent
some 22 years with them. -Yes.

02:13:09.404 --> 02:13:11.994
But, you married Rohit Kumar
against their wishes. Right?

02:13:12.586 --> 02:13:14.268
Yes. That's because I loved Rohit.

02:13:14.629 --> 02:13:15.629
I see.

02:13:16.258 --> 02:13:19.902
With whom, apart your parents have
you shared the longest relationship?

02:13:22.354 --> 02:13:25.543
-With my son Sunil, I think.
-You spent 5 years with him.

02:13:25.879 --> 02:13:27.788
And you've met him
only once afterwards!

02:13:27.924 --> 02:13:30.605
Now consider your husband. Don't
you think you've shared a...

02:13:30.685 --> 02:13:32.226
...very long
relationship with him?

02:13:34.664 --> 02:13:36.391
I didn't hear you, Ms. Kiran.

02:13:38.718 --> 02:13:41.171
-Yes. -And how many years in all,
prior to your marriage...

02:13:41.251 --> 02:13:43.294
...and afterwards have you
shared this relationship with him?

02:13:45.415 --> 02:13:51.815
-Nearly 7 years. -7 years!
Which means that you have failed...

02:13:52.357 --> 02:13:55.913
...to sustain a relationship by
marriage, a social institution...

02:13:56.063 --> 02:13:59.102
...that is held holy and of
irrevocable bondage in our culture!

02:13:59.182 --> 02:14:00.802
-Objection milord!
-Over ruled.

02:14:01.636 --> 02:14:04.872
-Please state your reply, Ms. Kiran.
-Tell us, Ms. Kiran...

02:14:05.014 --> 02:14:08.064
D'you agree that you've failed
to sustain the relationship.

02:14:09.353 --> 02:14:13.251
-No, I didn't fail. -Didn't you?!
Would you rate this as a success?

02:14:13.830 --> 02:14:18.386
-Your marriage is on the rocks.
-We have failed each other.

02:14:18.719 --> 02:14:21.279
Not "both of us", Ms. Kiran.
It's you. You have failed!

02:14:21.488 --> 02:14:23.595
You walked out on your husband.
He didn't.

02:14:23.868 --> 02:14:26.203
You failed the relationship.

02:14:28.904 --> 02:14:32.244
-It's the marriage which failed.
-Not the marriage. You failed!

02:14:32.640 --> 02:14:35.794
You've failed to sustain the most
precious relationship of your life.

02:14:36.480 --> 02:14:37.864
Is that true? Or, isn't it?

02:14:49.399 --> 02:14:52.724
-Say it aloud. I didn't hear you.
Is it true? Or, isn't it? -Yes.

02:14:53.354 --> 02:14:54.354
Your honour.

02:14:54.948 --> 02:14:57.680
She walked out on her
parents after 22 years.

02:14:58.157 --> 02:15:01.167
She walked out on her
husband for 7 years.

02:15:01.350 --> 02:15:06.453
What guarantee that she won't desert
her child after another 2 or 3 years?

02:15:33.008 --> 02:15:35.330
D'you think that your
case stands weakened now?

02:15:35.410 --> 02:15:36.993
-No comments please.
-One question.

02:15:37.203 --> 02:15:38.865
You haven't lost a single
suit till date, Mr. Bhojwani.

02:15:38.945 --> 02:15:41.849
-But it seems that you're going
to lose this one. -No comments please.

02:15:43.865 --> 02:15:44.865
Your honour.

02:15:46.737 --> 02:15:51.313
Generally, It's the woman who
is favored in disputes like this.

02:15:53.344 --> 02:15:56.152
That's because she's
a woman and a mother.

02:15:58.825 --> 02:16:01.489
But presently, the questions
revolve around the child.

02:16:03.438 --> 02:16:06.518
As I understand, this Court will
decide in the child's interest...

02:16:07.474 --> 02:16:10.691
...about what's good for Sunil.

02:16:12.818 --> 02:16:16.030
I've been looking after
him for nearly 2 years now.

02:16:17.153 --> 02:16:21.084
I've learnt something.
And, I have understood much.

02:16:23.795 --> 02:16:28.179
And slowly, I've understood what
it takes to be a good father.

02:16:29.891 --> 02:16:33.676
It takes patience. One needs to
spend a lot of time with the child.

02:16:35.152 --> 02:16:37.419
For hours, I've heard him
talk of strange fantasies.

02:16:37.947 --> 02:16:40.446
I'd get tired of listening to him.
But, I'd go on listening despite.

02:16:40.888 --> 02:16:42.705
One must reply to a thousand
questions he has to ask.

02:16:42.815 --> 02:16:46.667
One must be there with him whenever
need be, so he might not feel lonely.

02:16:50.481 --> 02:16:53.928
To do all that, one must love.

02:16:56.597 --> 02:17:04.885
And I don't know where it's written
that a woman can love more than a man.

02:17:08.052 --> 02:17:12.449
Must a mother always love the
child more than the father?

02:17:22.130 --> 02:17:25.840
I do not say that the child
cannot have a better upbringing.

02:17:27.704 --> 02:17:29.593
I've always tried my best.

02:17:32.081 --> 02:17:37.598
Sometimes I'd scold him and he'd
go to bed with a heavy heart.

02:17:40.089 --> 02:17:45.539
Up next morning, we'd have breakfast
together and we'd laugh and talk.

02:17:46.665 --> 02:17:48.366
It was all as if
nothing had happened.

02:17:49.709 --> 02:17:53.267
Later, I'd drop him to school.
And while returning from school...

02:17:53.741 --> 02:17:55.678
...he would tell me about what
had happened all day in school.

02:17:56.171 --> 02:17:57.921
We used to dine together.

02:17:59.718 --> 02:18:01.314
And afterwards
I'd tell him stories.

02:18:08.941 --> 02:18:13.747
We've created a world for ourselves.
And it took a lot of love to do that.

02:18:17.781 --> 02:18:22.464
If this is destroyed, we
can never build it again.

02:18:32.291 --> 02:18:33.841
Don't do this, Kiran.

02:18:36.767 --> 02:18:39.204
Please don't do this to me again.

02:18:50.246 --> 02:18:51.246
Rohit.

02:18:51.925 --> 02:18:59.490
You've told the court that it must
decide in the interest of your son.

02:19:00.037 --> 02:19:01.037
Yes.

02:19:01.300 --> 02:19:05.814
Did you work at the Copper Chimney
restaurant when you met Ms. Kiran?

02:19:05.959 --> 02:19:08.412
-Yes,
-How much salary did you draw then?

02:19:09.252 --> 02:19:10.395
3000 Rupees a month.

02:19:10.973 --> 02:19:12.314
3000 Rupees a month.

02:19:12.974 --> 02:19:14.767
But, you were dismissed
from the job, weren't you?

02:19:14.847 --> 02:19:17.775
I wasn't dismissed. I left
that job of my own volition.

02:19:18.105 --> 02:19:19.390
You left the job!

02:19:19.521 --> 02:19:21.385
And I thought that people take...

02:19:21.465 --> 02:19:23.354
...on greater
responsibilities after marriage!

02:19:23.433 --> 02:19:24.857
I wanted to rise in life.

02:19:25.424 --> 02:19:26.547
I wanted to become
a successful singer.

02:19:26.722 --> 02:19:29.233
You must've received
several offers for singing.

02:19:29.661 --> 02:19:31.594
I did get an offer
from Amar Kaushik.

02:19:32.120 --> 02:19:34.352
From Amar Kaushik! Lovely!

02:19:34.921 --> 02:19:39.595
But I don't think you have sung
in any of his films. Or, have you?

02:19:40.555 --> 02:19:42.397
-I had dropped the film.
-Left that too!

02:19:42.638 --> 02:19:43.638
Why?

02:19:46.010 --> 02:19:47.784
Differences had
cropped up between us.

02:19:47.864 --> 02:19:50.683
I see... differences! And
what did you do afterwards?

02:19:51.506 --> 02:19:53.050
I went back to the earlier job.

02:19:53.194 --> 02:19:55.219
-At Copper Chimney? -Yes.

02:19:55.770 --> 02:19:57.623
And how much salary were you paid?

02:20:01.806 --> 02:20:05.024
I didn't hear you, Mr. Rohit.
How much salary were you paid?

02:20:05.995 --> 02:20:09.946
-2500 rupees.
-2500?! Down from 3000 to 2500!

02:20:10.505 --> 02:20:16.625
You're the first person ever to
climb down the ladder to success.

02:20:20.710 --> 02:20:23.558
And I do not think it to
be in your son's interest.

02:20:24.018 --> 02:20:25.162
Anyway.

02:20:26.089 --> 02:20:34.868
On September 13, you tried to
rob 5000 rupees from the cashier.

02:20:35.001 --> 02:20:36.741
-Objection my lord.
-Overruled

02:20:36.821 --> 02:20:38.913
No. I didn't try to rob.
I was asking for a loan.

02:20:38.993 --> 02:20:42.822
You tried to take the money forcibly.
And when waiters in the restaurant...

02:20:42.902 --> 02:20:45.388
...tried to apprehend you,
you fought with them physically.

02:20:45.973 --> 02:20:47.925
I was merely taking a loan.
And I had intended to repay it.

02:20:48.005 --> 02:20:52.740
Not only fisticuffs. Furniture was
broken and the restaurant losses.

02:20:53.097 --> 02:20:57.678
For the crime, Mr. Rohit Kumar had
spend some time in a police-lockup.

02:20:57.818 --> 02:20:59.487
-Is it so, or, isn't it?
-Why don't you try to understand?

02:20:59.645 --> 02:21:02.744
Please reply to my question in
the affirmative or the negative.

02:21:02.942 --> 02:21:05.747
I'm trying to give a reply. And I can't
do that in a mere "yes" or "no".

02:21:06.031 --> 02:21:08.510
I was taking an advance. It was
to be deducted form my salary.

02:21:08.985 --> 02:21:12.782
My son had asked for gift on his
birthday. And, I promised the gift.

02:21:13.192 --> 02:21:16.424
Stop shouting! Else, this
court holds you for contempt.

02:21:17.946 --> 02:21:19.240
Mr. Bhojwani you may proceed.

02:21:20.034 --> 02:21:23.182
Were you confined in the
police lock up, or, weren't you?

02:21:25.518 --> 02:21:26.910
-Yes. I was confined.
-Good.

02:21:27.138 --> 02:21:34.304
-Now, do you consider yourself
to be a responsible father? -Yes.

02:21:34.820 --> 02:21:42.907
Was your son was about to lose an
eye because you were irresponsible?

02:21:42.987 --> 02:21:44.588
-Objection my lord.
-Overruled

02:21:44.668 --> 02:21:48.161
Was your son Sunil
about to lose an eye?

02:21:48.562 --> 02:21:50.289
He was playing in the park.
And he fell down.

02:21:50.369 --> 02:21:52.651
He fell down because
you were careless!

02:21:52.731 --> 02:21:57.302
-And he was about to lose on eye!
-It was an accident.

02:21:57.382 --> 02:22:00.855
-It could've happened to anyone.
-Didn't you tell Ms. Kiran that he...

02:22:00.935 --> 02:22:03.673
...fell down because
you were careless...

02:22:03.843 --> 02:22:06.365
...and that he was
about to lose an eye?

02:22:08.728 --> 02:22:11.410
Tell us, Mr. Rohit, is
it true? Or, isn't it?

02:22:16.197 --> 02:22:23.512
-Yes. -Do you concede that your son
could've lost an eye for your fault?

02:22:26.424 --> 02:22:27.907
Yes.
That's all your honour.

02:22:54.848 --> 02:22:57.418
I had no idea that my lawyer
would drag that into the court.

02:23:00.177 --> 02:23:02.223
He had asked me a lot of question.

02:23:03.573 --> 02:23:05.497
I had merely answered
his questions.

02:23:06.477 --> 02:23:09.041
I know you aren't at fault.

02:23:10.816 --> 02:23:14.370
Please believe me.
I didn't do it willingly.

02:23:15.284 --> 02:23:17.453
Rohit, Rohit please.

02:23:21.387 --> 02:23:25.230
After hearing the depositors made by
witnesses, this court has decided...

02:23:25.310 --> 02:23:28.995
...that the child Sunil Kumar be
placed under Mrs. Kiran's custody.

02:23:33.910 --> 02:23:34.913
Congratulations.

02:23:36.304 --> 02:23:37.573
Congratulations.

02:24:04.637 --> 02:24:06.797
Daddy! Daddy! Daddy!

02:24:07.591 --> 02:24:11.701
Vacations start from today.
It's a month long vacation!

02:24:12.012 --> 02:24:14.345
We'll go to Matheran during
the vacation, won't we?

02:24:15.737 --> 02:24:18.048
-Would you like an ice-cream?
-No. I want an ice-candy.

02:24:19.418 --> 02:24:20.418
Come on.

02:24:21.566 --> 02:24:24.880
Do you know something. Daddy? All
the kids in my class are going...

02:24:25.036 --> 02:24:27.037
...to Simla on a school trip.
But, I'm not going with them.

02:24:27.209 --> 02:24:32.464
I'll go to Matheran with you. We'll
have lots of fun out there, won't we?

02:24:35.573 --> 02:24:39.790
We'll fly kites over there. And
I'll carry the cricket kit with me too.

02:24:40.887 --> 02:24:45.862
"Believe this,
if tomorrow the whole world"

02:24:46.286 --> 02:24:50.006
"Does not stand by me"

02:24:51.446 --> 02:24:59.022
"Who then is the
companion of my journey?"

02:25:13.392 --> 02:25:14.392
Sonu!

02:25:15.666 --> 02:25:16.666
Yes.

02:25:16.888 --> 02:25:18.363
I want to tell you something.

02:25:31.210 --> 02:25:33.927
This is a present from me.
It's a seasoned ball.

02:25:34.444 --> 02:25:37.352
Do come over to play cricket.
We'll have a match.

02:25:37.576 --> 02:25:43.527
Oh yes. You'll play for my team.
And we'll beat the grocer's team.

02:25:43.761 --> 02:25:47.256
-Mr. Ramdayal called up to say
that the car is coming. -I see.

02:25:47.481 --> 02:25:48.730
Carry the luggage down.

02:25:49.420 --> 02:25:50.848
Let's go downstairs.

02:26:04.698 --> 02:26:10.233
Don't cry, Sonu. Come on. You'll
enjoy yourself at Mummy's house.

02:26:11.127 --> 02:26:12.776
You'll have lots
of toys over there.

02:26:13.673 --> 02:26:16.121
And I'll come down to see you too.

02:26:19.953 --> 02:26:20.999
C'mon cheer up.

02:26:22.045 --> 02:26:25.333
-Take him down, Farida. I'll be
with you in sometime. -Very well.

02:26:31.456 --> 02:26:32.784
Where's your bat, Sunil?

02:26:34.047 --> 02:26:35.997
Where's your bat?
He must've forgotten it.

02:26:36.155 --> 02:26:37.549
I'll fetch it.
-Come along, son.

02:27:36.408 --> 02:27:37.720
Sonu has gone downstairs.

02:27:39.092 --> 02:27:40.866
-I want to tell you something, Rohit.
-What?

02:27:46.303 --> 02:27:48.537
This is Sonu's bat.
He forgot to take it.

02:27:50.645 --> 02:27:52.415
I bought a full
cricket kit yesterday.

02:27:53.188 --> 02:27:55.234
Why?! Isn't this bat
good for him anymore?

02:27:55.808 --> 02:28:00.820
No. It's just that I remembered
that Sonu is fond of cricket.

02:28:01.463 --> 02:28:05.003
Not only that. I've bought him
all the toys he could ever want.

02:28:08.719 --> 02:28:12.123
I've made him a room that
looks just like the one here.

02:28:13.158 --> 02:28:15.279
The same bed; a small table;
and a similar cupboard.

02:28:16.240 --> 02:28:18.594
And I've painted the walls
the same shade of color.

02:28:22.837 --> 02:28:29.255
All because I want to
make Sonu feel at home.

02:28:34.739 --> 02:28:40.512
And then I realized
that this is his home.

02:28:43.741 --> 02:28:45.684
A few articles can't
make a home for anyone.

02:28:48.673 --> 02:28:53.023
Sonu stays here. This is his home.

02:29:19.833 --> 02:29:26.032
Over the past few days, our lives
and our sentiments were laid bare.

02:29:27.385 --> 02:29:30.850
You must've been hurt. I know that.

02:29:33.191 --> 02:29:36.982
And today I know that nothing
matters more than the relationship.

02:29:39.486 --> 02:29:43.810
I'm sorry for everything
that has happened.

02:29:48.363 --> 02:29:51.640
You're staying here,
Sonu... with your father.

02:29:57.806 --> 02:29:59.228
This is your home.

02:30:06.300 --> 02:30:07.391
Kiran..

02:30:12.430 --> 02:30:15.293
This is your home too.
